Summary:
Comprehensive Summary: OnePlus 11 5G - Navigating Brilliance and Caveats
 

 The OnePlus 11 5G, amid high expectations, presents a diverse spectrum of reviews that potential buyers should carefully consider. Here's a consolidated overview:
 

 Pros:
 

 Performance and Display: The Snapdragon 8 Gen 1 processor ensures a swift experience, complemented by a vibrant display with a 120Hz refresh rate and Dolby Vision support.
 Battery and Charging: The phone earns praise for its remarkable battery life and the standout feature of 100W fast charging, allowing a full charge in under 30 minutes.
 Camera System: The Hasselblad-backed camera system, especially the rear setup, is celebrated for exceptional photography and 8K video recording.
 Build and Design: Users appreciate the well-crafted device, noting its premium feel and the elegant marble finish.
 Software Updates: The promise of five years of software updates from OnePlus is seen as a positive commitment.
 Cons:
 

 Front Camera and Durability: Some users express dissatisfaction with the front camera's performance, particularly in low-light conditions. Durability concerns, including dead spots on the screen, are reported.
 Software Bugs: Notable reports highlight software bugs, suggesting the need for regular updates to address these issues.
 Competitor Comparisons: While competitive in its price range, the OnePlus 11 faces critiques for lacking features offered by competitors, such as wireless charging and IP ratings.
 Customer Support: Dissatisfaction with OnePlus customer support is mentioned, with users citing unresponsive service centers and difficulty in issue resolution under warranty.
 Conclusion:
 The OnePlus 11 5G emerges as a robust player in the smartphone market, delivering impressive performance, a stellar display, and a commendable camera system. However, potential buyers are cautioned to consider reported drawbacks like front camera concerns, software bugs, and durability issues. Acknowledging the phone's value for money, users are encouraged to stay informed about software updates and carefully evaluate their specific preferences and requirements before making a purchase.

Product Title: OnePlus 11 5G (Eternal Green, 16GB RAM, 256GB Storage)
Review Content: Purchased this product after lot of hesitation since I was using Samsung Galaxy S22+ for last 1 year. God! I am in love with this product. It's awesome all rounder phone & somewhat now my S22+ is sidelined. Comparison directly with S22+ : 1. Display: OP11 is more eye friendly & cherry on top is Dolby vision support so you are gonna enjoy multimedia consumption more on OP 11 than S22+ 2. Camera: S22+ will get a score of 10 but OP11 will bag 9 ( as front supports only 1080p). 3 Battery: OP 11 is clear winner you can rely on it as a daily driver with 100W charging support you don't have to worry for recharge. Recharges within 20 minutes when battery falls at 20%. 4. Performance: top notch is with OP 11 & OP 11 is clear winner 5. UI: Samsung is clear winner in this department. I would rate 10 while OP 11 will bag 9 for UI. 6. Value for money: OP 11 7. 5G & 4G network reception: OP 11 is way better than S22+ Call quality is clear on both in outdoor condition. 8. Speaker: OP 11 has more loud, clear & immersive speaker system. 9. IP rating: Samsung is clear winner 10. Wireless charging: Samsung has an edge but you will not feel it's loss since it is well supplemented by 100 W charger in the box. 11. Haptic feedback: OP 11 has clear advantage Conclusion: This is my first product of OnePlus after using Samsung S20FE 5G & S22+ & I am satisfied with this product. If you are planning to buy new phone & you have budget of 50-60K then you can consider it as a reliable phone & I would suggest opt for 16GB 256GB RAM variant since it comes with UFS 4.0 which will secure it's performance for 4 years atleast. Direct competitor of OP 11 are S22+ S23/S23+ iPhone 13/14 & Pixel 7 As a user I find pixel & iPhone have compromises in lacking telephoto lens & charging speed. I consider these features very useful especially when you are outdoor & clicking portrait of DSLR level.
Cause_1: OP11 is more eye friendly & cherry on top is Dolby vision support so you are gonna enjoy multimedia consumption more on OP 11 than S22+
Cause_2: OP 11 has more loud, clear & immersive speaker system.
Cause_3: OP 11 is clear winner you can rely on it as a daily driver with 100W charging support you don't have to worry for recharge. Recharges within 20 minutes when battery falls at 20%
Cause_4: top notch is with OP 11 & OP 11 is clear winner

Product Title: OnePlus 11 5G (Eternal Green, 16GB RAM, 256GB Storage)
Review Content: As an avid tech enthusiast, I was thrilled to get my hands on the new OnePlus 11 5G. And let me tell you, it did not disappoint. First of all, the design of this phone is sleek and modern, with a large 6.7-inch display that makes everything from streaming videos to scrolling through social media a joy. Plus, the 120Hz refresh rate ensures smooth and seamless performance. But what really impressed me was the camera. The OnePlus 11 5G boasts a triple-lens rear camera with a whopping 108MP primary sensor, making it one of the most powerful camera setups on the market. And let me tell you, the photos I took with this phone were absolutely stunning. The battery life is also impressive, lasting all day with heavy use, and the fast charging feature means you can get back to full power in no time. And with 5G capabilities, this phone is future-proofed and ready for whatever comes next. Overall, I highly recommend the OnePlus 11 5G for anyone in the market for a new phone. It's a powerful and stylish device that is sure to impress. In terms of performance, the OnePlus 11 5G is a true powerhouse. With its Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Gen 1 processor and up to 16GB of RAM, this phone is capable of handling even the most demanding tasks with ease. Apps open quickly, multitasking is a breeze, and gaming is incredibly smooth and responsive. the OnePlus 11 5G is an outstanding phone that truly delivers on all fronts. If you're in the market for a new smartphone and want the very best in design, performance, and camera technology, then look no further than the OnePlus 11 5G. It's a true masterpiece that is sure to impress even the most discerning tech enthusiast.

Product Title: OnePlus 11 5G (Eternal Green, 16GB RAM, 256GB Storage)
Review Content: Performance: pretty fast, we did not see any lag in a week's use. face unlock and touch unlock are as fast as an iphone's. you can open many applications but phone will not break a sweat. new processor has really done a good job, with practical 16gb of ram. Security: it provides lots of security features for locking phone: face unlock, pattern, password, number lock and fingerprint. Screen: It has a very bright screen which works well indoors. little dark under the sun, but I feel it is ok. curved screen gives it a good look. Camera: Picture quality from back camera is decent, only drawback is it overexposes photos some times, so white balance needs to be adjusted before taking photos. same goes for front camera. telephoto and macro modes do a decent job. front facing camera takes decent pictures, but photos are patchy and have excess sharpness in low light mode. video calls have decent quality. Connectivity: 4G and 4G connectivity is great and there is no apparent lag in network. 5G gave around 100Mbps speed on ookla. Battery: battery backup is decent and phone lasts for a day with moderate use. new processor is fast and phone does not heat up when charging or during overuse as our previous oneplus 5. 100W charger is good and charges full phone in under 30 min in practical scenario, without heating phone. Build: phone is little at bulky side, feeling of which will disappear when you are used to it. Phone is pretty sturdy and looks good when held in one hand. overall a good purchase.

Product Title: OnePlus 11 5G (Eternal Green, 16GB RAM, 256GB Storage)
Review Content: Upgraded my phone, the last phone I had bought was Asus Zenfone 5z, back in 2018, and it was a banger. Fast forward 2023, I decided to buy a phone as my phone was quite dated. Had several options in mind, including, Asus zenfone 9, iPhone 14, samsung s23, pixel 7pro, iqoo and then some more.. Finally went with one plus, though I had to compromise on wireless charging, no headphone jack. I must say it's value for money, it might not be as feature packed as samsung s23 ultra or iPhone 14, but it is a great phone none the less. The things I liked the most about OnePlus 11(bought 256 GB,16 GB variant)- -Camera is great -Snapdragon gen 2 is quick at multitasking -Display is beyond words for me -The updates that I am getting(till Android 17+1 year security update extra) -refresh rate really makes difference -absolutely no lag while gaming -great battery backup -very fast charging (though I recommend to switch to normal charging for longer battery life) There is only one issue I faced once when the file manager did not open for some reason, but it was a one time glitch I think.. All in all I would say, I can live without wireless charging and headphone jack(will be using Asus Zenfone 5z for wired listening), saved a lot of money over competition while comprising very little. Anyone having any doubt can follow my advice , you are making the right decision..

Product Title: OnePlus 11 5G (Eternal Green, 16GB RAM, 256GB Storage)
Review Content: Amazing Specs. All round good phone. Everything is positive about it. The only cons are the front camera is a bit average for 60k. It's not bad but it's not at 60k level. In the portrait photos, the skin tones are not accurate. It tends to lighten up the skin colour more often than not which kind of bothers me. So these are the 2 things you've to keep in mind. If you're ready to deal with these cons, you will enjoy this phone everyday in your life. You will always feel so happy to purchase this beautiful phone. I've hardly faced any issues after 6 months.

Product Title: OnePlus 11 5G (Eternal Green, 16GB RAM, 256GB Storage)
Review Content: I was an iPhone user but for some personal reasons had to switch to android and bought this on 6th March 2023. As it was a brand new model in the market I couldn't find any decent back cover in the market or online so using the cover provided in the box. Few weeks later the phone dropped from e height of 2-3 ft. approx and later I noticed there is a small dent on the top righr of the back panel. Now I have used more delicate phones (iPhone 5S. 6s. 8. XR. 12 mini and 13) so I have always been careful but this OnePlus built is awful and the pictures are yellowish. I have tried every camera settings and went to the store as well but all in vain.

Product Title: OnePlus 11 5G (Eternal Green, 16GB RAM, 256GB Storage)
Review Content: The media could not be loaded. Excellent device for the price. I'm writing this stubby review and will use it as a running log to report the good and bad about the device. Until now, the phone feels great! Definitely feels like the old OnePlus of yore, and the good part, thankfully. The handfeel is very good, it masks the weight and size of the device, designed quite well. It's a joy to type on (fabulous haptics!). The screen is really good. The battery life seems to be holding up well (using on qHD + 120hz). It did heat up during the initial setup but calmed right down after a while. Not heatup up during normal usage. Did get warmish during a Super-Sus session (not blazing hot, just warmish). Will report specifics after using it for a few days. Received the device today (16/02/2023).

Product Title: OnePlus 11 5G (Eternal Green, 16GB RAM, 256GB Storage)
Review Content: Performance: 10/10 it's really fast. The display touch is snappy and instantly responds to your touchs no delay no matter you are doing heavy gaming or using normally. Display: 10/10 The display shines and OMG the 120hz just use it once and you will never go back. The colour are really good and calibrated specially if you are watching HDR content. The text is crisp and clear. Brightness is really good. Sound: 8/10 Sound on loudspeaker is loud and bassy but sometimes it distorts on higher volume but that can be fixed via OTA update. Camera: 10/10 I don't use phone camera that much but yes it's better than my last phone OnePlus 7 Pro. Build quality: 10/10 Build quality is really good and it feels that you are holding a premium device and it's heavy. Charging: 10/10 The 100w charger OMG. It charges so fast Just take a nap or watch an 15m video and the phone is 100% charged. Battery: 10/10 The battery easily lasts 1+ for normal usage/ 5-6 hours of continuous gaming depending on your in games settings and display resolution.

Product Title: OnePlus 11 5G (Eternal Green, 16GB RAM, 256GB Storage)
Review Content: I've moved to OP11 from OP 7t pro and there's not much difference. In fact 7t pro feels much premium when you hold these two together. It's not worth spending 62K on a phone which doesn't stand out from its previous models. OP11 has a better camera and touch is bit fast but again it's not the best. They should've come up with way better and precise hardware. UI is the same old which will not let you feel anything brand new. Bettery is always good enough in the initial stages as it was for the OP 7t pro but got downgraded later. This is something all brands do to their previous phones so that new sets could be sold. That's it for now. Will update more as it gets old. NOTE- Never pre-order anything over amazon.

Product Title: OnePlus 11 5G (Eternal Green, 16GB RAM, 256GB Storage)
Review Content: I have been a OnePlus user for past 4 generations. I had OP7pro, OP8T, OP9 and finally got the OP11. After the OP7Tpro the other devices were good but not as good as the OP7pro. I got this phone only because we don't have many options left in android and I am anti-iOS guy. However, this phone amazed me like anything. It is as good as the old OP devices. The company went all out on this one. Pros: >Best OP camera (probably one of the best in this price range) >SD 8 Gen 2 makes the phone lightining fast > Feels premium > Fluid display > Amazong battery backup with really fast charging Cons: > Wireless charging missing which was in the OP10pro. > 4k @ 120fps missing which was again in the 10pro but not on this one > IP64 this one is a real bummer even my OP8T was IP68.
Cause_1: Wireless charging missing which was in the OP10pro.
Cause_2: Fluid display .Feels premium
Cause_3: Amazong battery backup with really fast charging
Cause_4: Best OP camera (probably one of the best in this price range) SD 8 Gen 2 makes the phone lightining fast

Review Content: The media could not be loaded. Update: On 30th September. The phone camera stopped working once again. I went to service center, they said they'll replace the whole camera. Since that day I have called multiple times and they're saying the parts are not delivered yet. I bought this phone from Amazon, and I got it on 25 August 2023. Since then, I have been using it usually, neither a heavy user nor a gamer. On 10 September 2023, suddenly the camera stopped working. I talked to customer care they told me to factory reset the phone. I did that, and there was no change. So on 11 September, I went to the authorized service center and they opened the phone to fix the camera. They said, 'It's a manufacturing defect and your phone is now older than 15 days so we can't replace it'. The problem is solved for now and if you face any hardware problem you can visit again. My point is it's a flagship phone which they launched almost 5 months ago and it has a manufacturing defect. It just costs more than 60,000 rupees and this is the kind of product they are selling under the name of the flagship. This phone is a collaboration with Hasselblad and it's meant for photography and videography.

Product Title: OnePlus 11 5G (Eternal Green, 16GB RAM, 256GB Storage)
Review Content: This was my 3rd OnePlus devices, from the earlier ones 5T and 9R. I bought At 62,000/- (having exchange for 5T for 8600 and rest from my card for the 16 GB and 256. But there are many issues with this phone: the volume buttons on the phone do not work: Just after using the phone for 2 days the lower volume button stop working and withing 5-10 min the up volume button is also not working. I have very bad experience with Amazon too, giving multiple calls and everytime the phone went on hold by the executive and then disconnected. I placed a return request and got on call with a technician, he requested me to install the minspect app. I did and they got the result that the volume keys are not working. Then they inform me that that they will send a technician to inspect the phone after a week time as no technician is available before that. My old phone which I put on exchange was working perfectly, but when I ask to return me my old phone, the Amazon team has refuse to do that. This has caused me a good amount of trouble as now I am left without a phone. Also I have even not received my old phone full amount, Amazon has sent only 3600 out of 8600. This is very bad experience with Amazon return service. I should be given full 8600. This is very troublesome. I would recommend not buy this phone from Amazon as the phone built quality and performance is not good, If one should spend 62,000, a good phone was expected from Amazon and One Plus. Complete waste of money and time.

Product Title: OnePlus 11 5G (Eternal Green, 16GB RAM, 256GB Storage)
Review Content: The media could not be loaded. The screen is supposed to have the same brightness level as a Iqoo 7 Legend, however if you compare both side by side, you will notice the Iqoo 7 being brighter. The Android flavour you get is modded in all the wrong places. So the best of Android experience is left out. The volume buttons on the phone do not work, and the phone wasn't even used as a daily driver! Now the Amazon experience is not what I expected. I placed a return request and got on call with a technician l, they requested me to install the mInspect app. I did and they got the result that the volume keys are not working. Then they inform that the brand will send it's technician to inspect the phone. And the amazing technician without visiting my place marked my case as solved and the phone is in perfect condition. I see the status of my service inspection as completed even though the person didn't come and guessed this was what happened. So I call the customer care and informed them that this is a fraudulent activity and that no one came to inspect. So now they are requesting me to wait for another week for a follow up by another technician. This has caused me a good amount of trouble as I am left without a phone. You can see the video attached as proof that the volume rocker doesn't work! I would recommend others to not buy this phone from Amazon as the return policy is not user friendly, rather seller friendly!
Cause_1: The media could not be loaded.
Cause_2: The screen is supposed to have the same brightness level as a Iqoo 7 Legend, however if you compare both side by side, you will notice the Iqoo 7 being brighter.
Cause_3: The Android flavour you get is modded in all the wrong places. So the best of Android experience is left out. The volume buttons on the phone do not work, and the phone wasn't even used as a daily driver! Now the Amazon experience is not what I expected.

Then they inform that the brand will send it's technician to inspect the phone. And the amazing technician without visiting my place marked my case as solved and the phone is in perfect condition. I see the status of my service inspection as completed even though the person didn't come and guessed this was what happened. So I call the customer care and informed them that this is a fraudulent activity and that no one came to inspect. So now they are requesting me to wait for another week for a follow up by another technician. This has caused me a good amount of trouble as I am left without a phone. You can see the video attached as proof that the volume rocker doesn't work! I would recommend others to not buy this phone from Amazon as the return policy is not user friendly, rather seller friendly!

Summary:
Final Summary Review: iPhone 13 and iPhone 14 Pro
 

 iPhone 13:
 The iPhone 13 receives widespread acclaim for its remarkable features, especially during festive sales. Customers praise the device for its sleek design, vibrant Midnight color, and impressive A15 Bionic chip performance. The camera system, battery life, and Super Retina XDR display contribute to a satisfying user experience. Some users note a few drawbacks, including a minor heating issue and the absence of a charger. Overall, the iPhone 13 is highly recommended for those entering the Apple ecosystem or looking for a premium smartphone.
 

 iPhone 14 Pro:
 The iPhone 14 Pro, an upgrade for many, is recognized for its incredible camera capabilities, A16 Bionic chip, and the innovative Dynamic Island. Users appreciate the phone's performance, immersive display with ProMotion technology, and impressive sound quality. However, there are reports of heating issues during usage and concerns about the battery life. While the device is commended for its premium build and fluid interface, some suggest waiting for the iPhone 15 or opting for the larger 14 Pro Max for better battery life and display size.
 

 In conclusion, both the iPhone 13 and iPhone 14 Pro offer a premium smartphone experience, with the choice depending on individual preferences, budget considerations, and the desire for the latest features. Prospective buyers are encouraged to explore various reviews and prioritize their needs before making a purchase decision.

Product Title: Apple iPhone 13 (128GB) - Blue
Review Content: 7 Days used review . The ordering experience in the greate indian sale was worst . I planned to buy this for 45999/- in oct7 greate indian sale offer but i got canceled then i bought for 48999 that was disppointed . Coming to phone IOS 16.6 (current not updated) - it was great, super handy for me, little feeling of weight . Display - The 60Hz refresh rate didn't felt badly form me cause i am used such kind of device before. - The brightness Range is so comfortable. - The 2160p60 HDR videos in youtube give blissful experiance Battery And charging - The charging time:- i took 1Hour to charge from 20% to 91% using apple 20w original adapter without any interruption - Battery backup - I am mostly maintain battery in btw 20% <-> 80% so i think this may get one day backup for me ,Average 5h screen on time - Little temperature warming while charging , no heating issue Perfomance - Good perfomance for video editing ,photography , social media . (I am not a gamer ) Camera - The cinematic Mode is mind Blowing . i missed 13 pro or higher varients for zooming in this mode . - Actually i really miss pro variant for the tele lens and camera features while i using this . Cost is wall for me. - The photos are nice and feature like exposure adjust and filter was good and quality photos . And the 5x zoomed photos is not good for me.it reduced the pixel quality . - The video and optical image stabilisation was mind blowing . i mostly explore on videos . it was soo good , no words other than that. AND THE BIGGEST FEAR FOR ME NOW IS IOS UPDATE i turned off the auto update at first place . i heared about DISPLAY ISSUES,HEATING ISSUES and BUGS in the ios updates for 13 and 14 series. So for expencive and established brand like apple does not fair . This is the only -ve i have to say as a reminder .Also i heared without ios update display issues are happened . Buy the way it is a hardware issue one of the display provider company's batch may show the issues . but we customers cannot identify which company provides the hardaware. I will attach my battery analytics data screnshot photo here so you can better understand how the battery is good

Product Title: Apple iPhone 14 Pro (256 GB) - Silver
Review Content: I upgraded from OnePlus 7 Pro and I am already familiar with iOS as I had iPhone 6 before that. I bought 14 Pro solely for its camera. I am someone who does a lot of mobile photography. The rest of the features are good but I am going to talk about camera and battery life. Battery life is decent for a compact phone, it lasts almost a day depending on your usage. Moving to the cameras, I feel it lacks a bit there. Don’t get me wrong, it’s good enough if you’re someone who does casual photography but if you belong to the category of nitpickers, the images produced are contrasty which you might consider a good thing but the shadows are way too crush and the phone also lacks at night photography compared to the competition. Other than that, the overall smartphone is great but if you’re someone who prefers better battery life and bigger display, consider iPhone 14 Pro Max or simply wait for the 15 series.

Summary:
Overall, the Samsung Galaxy Note 10+ receives overwhelmingly positive reviews from customers, highlighting its impressive features and performance. Users praise the device for its outstanding screen resolution, powerful battery life, and fast charging capabilities. The camera quality is a standout feature, with users expressing satisfaction with both front and rear cameras, especially for capturing high-quality photos and videos. The S Pen functionality is widely appreciated, being described as fantastic and serving both creative and productivity purposes.
 

 While some users mention that the phone is a bit large, the majority find it comfortable to hold, and the design is considered premium and stylish. The aura glow color is particularly praised for its attractiveness. Users note that the phone is customizable and performs well under various conditions, making it a versatile choice for different tasks. The seamless gaming performance and the absence of a headphone jack are minor drawbacks mentioned, but they do not significantly impact the overall positive experience.
 

 There are a few negative reviews, such as complaints about the on-screen fingerprint scanner requiring a hard press at times and concerns about potential performance deterioration after two years of use. However, these criticisms are outweighed by the numerous positive comments about the device's speed, features, and display quality.
 

 In summary, the Samsung Galaxy Note 10+ is widely regarded as an excellent flagship smartphone, offering a premium experience with its impressive display, versatile camera system, S Pen functionality, and overall high performance. The positive feedback from users suggests that it is a valuable investment for those seeking a top-tier device with advanced features.

Summary:
Overall, the Samsung Galaxy Note 10+ receives overwhelmingly positive reviews from customers, highlighting its impressive features and performance. Users praise the device for its outstanding screen resolution, powerful battery life, and fast charging capabilities. The camera quality is a standout feature, with users expressing satisfaction with both front and rear cameras, especially for capturing high-quality photos and videos. The S Pen functionality is widely appreciated, being described as fantastic and serving both creative and productivity purposes.
 

 While some users mention that the phone is a bit large, the majority find it comfortable to hold, and the design is considered premium and stylish. The aura glow color is particularly praised for its attractiveness. Users note that the phone is customizable and performs well under various conditions, making it a versatile choice for different tasks. The seamless gaming performance and the absence of a headphone jack are minor drawbacks mentioned, but they do not significantly impact the overall positive experience.
 

 There are a few negative reviews, such as complaints about the on-screen fingerprint scanner requiring a hard press at times and concerns about potential performance deterioration after two years of use. However, these criticisms are outweighed by the numerous positive comments about the device's speed, features, and display quality.
 

 In summary, the Samsung Galaxy Note 10+ is widely regarded as an excellent flagship smartphone, offering a premium experience with its impressive display, versatile camera system, S Pen functionality, and overall high performance. The positive feedback from users suggests that it is a valuable investment for those seeking a top-tier device with advanced features.

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Note10+ (Aura Black, 12GB RAM, 256GB Storage)
Review Content: Samsung Galaxy Note 10+ is an excellent phone and we quite like what Samsung is pitching. The Notes are meant to be big and bold, and true to the theme, the Note 10 Plus delivers powerful hardware and a premium experience. It’s still an incremental update over what we had last year, but the more we use it – the more we can appreciate the nuances. The Note 10+ has a fabulous display, a thoughtful, slim design, smart OneUI software, simpler Dex implementation, and improved fast charging. It’s also the most comfortable big phone that we have used this year. Pixel 4 and iPhone 11 Pro still might have an edge when it comes to still or rather portrait photography, but the Note 10+ too has a great camera and should be particularly appealing to videographers. It’s also our personal favorite Android phone for 2019.
Cause_1: Samsung Galaxy Note 10+ is an excellent phone and we quite like what Samsung is pitching. The Notes are meant to be big and bold, and true to the theme, the Note 10 Plus delivers powerful hardware and a premium experience. It’s still an incremental update over what we had last year, but the more we use it – the more we can appreciate the nuances.
Cause_2: The Note 10+ has a fabulous display, a thoughtful, slim design,
Cause_3: smart OneUI software, simpler Dex implementation,
Cause_4: and improved fast charging.
Cause_5: It’s also the most comfortable big phone that we have used this year. Pixel 4 and iPhone 11 Pro still might have an edge when it comes to still or rather portrait photography, but the Note 10+ too has a great camera and should be particularly appealing to videographers. It’s also our personal favorite Android phone for 2019.

Summary Review for Oppo:
 

 Oppo presents a mixed bag of reviews for its F23 5G model. While some users express satisfaction with timely delivery, good packaging, and the phone's features, others raise concerns about certain aspects.
 

 Positive feedback includes the phone's slim design, ultravolume mode for gamers, microscopic lens, and the impressive Supervooc charging, which, according to users, is exceptionally fast. The phone's sound quality, fingerprint sensor, and overall performance also receive favorable mentions.
 

 On the downside, there are reports of product damage upon delivery, incorrect chargers being provided, and issues with the camera quality. Some users express dissatisfaction with Oppo's charging time, suggesting a decrease in efficiency with prolonged use, as well as complaints about display issues.
 

 The F23 5G model is praised for its camera capabilities, particularly the microlens providing unique perspectives. However, there are concerns about the front camera's quality. Users appreciate the large internal memory of 256GB but express mixed opinions about the battery life, with some claiming it needs to be charged only once a day, while others complain about rapid depletion.
 

 In conclusion, the Oppo F23 5G appears to offer a mix of positive and negative experiences. While it boasts several commendable features, some users encounter issues related to product quality, charging efficiency, and camera performance. Prospective buyers may want to weigh these aspects carefully before making a purchase decision.

Review Content: I recently purchased the Boat Airdopes, and I must say, they have exceeded my expectations in every way. These wireless earbuds are an absolute delight to use, and here's why: First and foremost, the sound quality is outstanding. The Boat Airdopes deliver crisp, clear audio with impressive bass. Whether I'm listening to my favorite music or taking calls, the sound is immersive and enjoyable. I appreciate how well-balanced the audio is, allowing me to truly appreciate the details in each song. The design of the Boat Airdopes is sleek and stylish. They fit snugly in my ears and provide a comfortable wearing experience. The earbuds are lightweight and don't cause any discomfort, even during extended periods of use. Additionally, they come with different-sized ear tips, ensuring a perfect fit for anyone. The wireless connectivity is seamless, and the Bluetooth pairing process is quick and hassle-free. Once connected, the Boat Airdopes maintain a strong and stable connection without any audio dropouts. I can freely move around without worrying about signal loss, which is incredibly convenient. Battery life is also impressive. The Boat Airdopes provide a long-lasting listening experience, allowing me to enjoy my music throughout the day without the need for frequent recharging. The charging case is compact and portable, making it easy to carry around and providing additional battery backup when needed. One feature I particularly appreciate is the touch controls on the earbuds. They are intuitive and responsive, allowing me to play/pause music, adjust the volume, and answer/reject calls with just a few taps. I love the convenience and simplicity this provides, eliminating the need to constantly reach for my phone. The Boat Airdopes also offer water and sweat resistance, making them ideal for workouts and outdoor activities. I have used them during my workouts, and they have stayed securely in place while delivering excellent sound quality. Lastly, the price point of the Boat Airdopes is highly competitive, especially considering the features and quality they offer. It's a great value for the money, and I can confidently say that these earbuds are worth every penny. In conclusion, the Boat Airdopes have truly impressed me with their exceptional sound quality, comfortable fit, seamless connectivity, and user-friendly features. They are a fantastic choice for anyone in search of reliable wireless earbuds. I highly recommend the Boat Airdopes to music enthusiasts and on-the-go individuals who want a superior audio experience without compromising on style or functionality

Product Title: JBL Tune 230NC TWS, Active Noise Cancellation Earbuds with Mic, Massive 40 Hrs Playtime with Speed Charge, Adjustable EQ APP, 4Mics for Perfect Calls, Google Fast Pair, Bluetooth 5.2 (Black)
Review Content: The media could not be loaded. Update: The right bud is facing issue it doesn't turn off even after in case. There are many who are facing this problem with right bud check google and youtube. DON'T BUY THESE EARPODS or you'll waste money. While researching for a good TWS with good ANC. I had two options. JBL 230NC and oneplus Z2. I opted for JBL as this is a brand built around sound and music. For a price tag of 5299, the sound was quite good. I like the sound good highs and lows, bass. You can customize it in the app. (Coming on the app later) The ANC worked very well. I commute alot in metro and traffic. It does a decent job of cutting off the audio, so you can hear your music without the sound of a child crying beside your seat. It also has aware mode and talk through mode also which is quite good. Aware mode disables ANC so you can hear the surrounding noise, good when you're walking beside a road or crossing it. Talk through mode also suppress the music playing and lets in extra noise from the outside. So it's making it easier to talk to someone without talking out your jbl tunes. But if there's wind then the mic let's in the wind sound to the point where you won't be able to listen anything else than the wind, making this feature useless. It should have a in-ear detection feature for this price. Coming to the app. Oh boy! Am I disappointed. I have a samsung galaxy s10 lite. The app is so so un optimized. It takes 10-15 sec to start the app and select my already paired tws. Even need to disconnect and connect bluetooth again. Then If i kill the app the tws starts behaving weird. It starts cutting off every 5 secs for like 2 secs. I start the app again and it fixes. Not always but not even that rarely. The range is so low that if you have one tws in your ear you cannot go to another room with the audio getting lagged every 5 seconds. The overall quantity of the product is not bad. Find my buds feature has helped me alot. I forget where my other bud is most of the time. The sound is pretty good. ANC is pretty good. Aware is good for safety. No call issues. Clear and crisp. The battery life is great. I charge my case after 3 days. Even though I listen to music for like 4-5 hours everyday. App equalizer can customize the sound according to your preferences. Only the app which is supposed to make it better tends to make me regret my decision of this purchase.

Product Title: JBL Tune 230NC TWS, Active Noise Cancellation Earbuds with Mic, Massive 40 Hrs Playtime with Speed Charge, Adjustable EQ APP, 4Mics for Perfect Calls, Google Fast Pair, Bluetooth 5.2 (Black)
Review Content: Received on 10 May 2022 and i am writing this review on 12th May, so, not enough time to get to the core of its performance but i shall note what caught my eye. Pros: 1. Music lovers will surely love this earbud because the clarity was awesome with ample bass as well. Full volume doesnt make the sound dither. Its just superb. I used a preset eq using the app too and selected VOCAL to get that extra clarity. Other modes are available to try too. Also settings changed to Audio instead of normal or video. 2. Video lip sync - no complaint there too. All good 3. There is this "talk thru" under ambience mode which i used through the app and its amazing because once the ear bud is in the ear, naturally you will feel like ear is blocked from outside noise right? Put this talk thru option and instantly you will feel like a hole has been created within the buds and you can hear everything around you. Its amazing 4. Call clarity should be awesome because i used a lot for making calls, work related mainly and no one complained about anything from the other side. May be because of this, i havent tried noise cancellation too. Most of my calls were while in a cabin in office. 5. Battery backup seems to be top notch too since i have used to watch videos and for calls, it doesnt deplete just like that. Cons: 1. When playing music the pausing does incur a slight milli second delay. Whether you pause on the buds or on the phone. Same for changing tracks. The above are my findings so far. The buds fits well for me. When you see its shape we might have a feeling it wont but it will. Case is cute and not bulky too. Overall, its just awesome for the price and you get JBL signature sound too.

Product Title: JBL Tune 230NC TWS, Active Noise Cancellation Earbuds with Mic, Massive 40 Hrs Playtime with Speed Charge, Adjustable EQ APP, 4Mics for Perfect Calls, Google Fast Pair, Bluetooth 5.2 (Black)
Review Content: The media could not be loaded. Pros: • I must say that these are one of the most extraordinary TWS in the market today. The price range is a little high, but it's worth it if you're a true music lover. • The noise cancellation is simply awesome! For this price range, it's worth it. • The battery backup is also nice. I am using these buds for a month now and charged them 3 times only. Battery goes for 9-10 days smoothly with 3-4 hours of daily use. 🔋👐 • You have to download the JBL app from the app store or play store and sync your TWS with your phone. Then only, you can use it. • From the app, you can select the audio or video mode for your buds depending on what you're listening to! • You can also select customized equalizers and gestures for each bud. • Google Assistant works nicely on these buds. • The most interesting feature is "Find My Buds". From your phone app, when you choose this option and if your buds are not in a case but linked to your phone, then you will hear a noisy alarm sound from buds which is quite audible from one room to another. So, it's useful if you have a habit of forgetting your buds anywhere in the home. Also, once your buds are out of the case, they connect to the device automatically and quickly. • I am a little possessive about my electronic devices hence I have purchased a cover for these buds separately from Amazon. I recommend the same to everyone. Cons: • Only one point could be a deciding factor for you before you buy the product, and that is its price. If it's within your budget, then you can surely go for this product! 👍

Product Title: JBL Tune 230NC TWS, Active Noise Cancellation Earbuds with Mic, Massive 40 Hrs Playtime with Speed Charge, Adjustable EQ APP, 4Mics for Perfect Calls, Google Fast Pair, Bluetooth 5.2 (Black)
Review Content: Bought during dasara sale for 3799 Rs. Excellent sound, has good bass, using with my Realme GT master Edition. ANC (5/5) The best thing about this is the ANC. It almost cancels all the noise out when you turn ANC. Another best feature is that we can switch between Ambient ANC, which does not filter all the noises. This feature is given when we are listening to music while walking on road to listen to oncoming vehicles. Connectivity (5/5) Connectivity is awesome, audio and video sync is excellent without any delay, tried in Netflix and Youtube. Calls (5/5) Coming to the calls, the audio is very clear when someone calls. Even voice from mic of TWS is excellent and can be heard to receiver's end without any distortion. Music (5/5) I listen to lot of music, and the quality is just out of the world. Has a dedicated equilizer in app, and can be tweaked around. Has proper Bass effect required for music, not over powering though. Overall Best for Music no doubt about. It is JBL after all. Comfort (5/5) I bought TWS 230 initially and returned it because of discomfort. Then I bought 130 TWS. Comfort wise I did not find any ear pain or discomfort even after wearing it for long time. The only problem is you cant hear the outside world if ANC is turned on. Its so good. For my Ear it fits perfectly medium sized ears. Battery (5/5) I charge the case once in a week for 10 mins. The case charges very fast with my phone charger. Cons The only Con is found is the case. The Lid on the case is bit loose. It can break easily if the case falls on the floor. Also Frequent opening of the Lid on the case makes the spring/ screw loose. Another con is that I was not able to find a pouch for this model anywhere. Then i had order from third party website. If you get it for 3.8k then definitely go for it. 230 NC also has same quality music, but has a bigger battery. According to me, this is a Bang for the Buck!.

Yes now on battery update it has been 10 days since I charged I don't use it everyday whole day I just use it while going out and to listen some music and case battery still has 70% I think u can guess how much I use I don't think the case is that beautiful it's ok if there wasn't a JBL branding on it this would like some cheap case and earbuds I guess the branding hypes the overall design, but for me both case design and buds design are satisfactory. Music feels good for the price point it's actually very nice.for some people it may fit very nice but for me oily ears it fits good but sometimes it feels falling it's ok because most of the earbuds doesn't fit me so I don't think this would be a problem for anybody except me. I bought this especially for listening music for that it's more than worth it. I have just used this for few hours I can't talk about battery as of now. But man ANC works beautifully. Update on battery life : there is no earbuds in market that would give battery life like this would give,music is fantastic, i would suggest if anyone thinking of buying earbuds i would suggest JBL and JBL only.

Product Title: JBL Tune 230NC TWS, Active Noise Cancellation Earbuds with Mic, Massive 40 Hrs Playtime with Speed Charge, Adjustable EQ APP, 4Mics for Perfect Calls, Google Fast Pair, Bluetooth 5.2 (Black)
Review Content: I’m writing this review after 1 week complete use: Pro’s: 1. Huge battery life. 2. Superb sound quality. 3. Call quality and ANC is good no complaints. 4. App supports is cherry on the cake. 5. Touch are smooth fast makes it more convenient to use. 6. Talk through feature is the best and very useful. 7. Light weight (tip : use the correct fit rubber tip which fits your ear) Con’s: 1. Case can catch scratches case cover is not found locally . 2. Anc while liestning to music or watching movies does not cut the surrounding sound that great. You can hear your surrounding sound. 3. Case top lid fills very light and thin needed to be thick at this price point. 4. Needed more equalizer options.

Product Title: JBL Tune 230NC TWS, Active Noise Cancellation Earbuds with Mic, Massive 40 Hrs Playtime with Speed Charge, Adjustable EQ APP, 4Mics for Perfect Calls, Google Fast Pair, Bluetooth 5.2 (Black)
Review Content: What can I say, everything is awesome.... Before I say anything about it, let me tell you guys that you need to download an APP called "JBL HEADPHONES" if you want to equalize as per your choice. There are lots of benefits that comes along with this app......you can even search for your lost side of earphones by playing an alarm from that app. There's a google assistant assigned on the left earphone which you can use over other app and it wont interfere with the current application that you are using in your mobile. And NOISE CANCELLATION is so perfect, as soon as you put on it blocks the air and noise to come inside the ear. It's been over 2 months and I'm loving everything. I hope it last for as many years as it can go on under my sweet care 🤗

Product Title: JBL Tune 230NC TWS, Active Noise Cancellation Earbuds with Mic, Massive 40 Hrs Playtime with Speed Charge, Adjustable EQ APP, 4Mics for Perfect Calls, Google Fast Pair, Bluetooth 5.2 (Black)
Review Content: This is a product review I wrote after using the product for 20+ days or more. Pros: 1. Aesthetically appealing 2. ANC reduces surrounding noise by at least 30% (when nothing is playing) and by up to 80% when something is playing. 3. The simple touch function for switching between tracks and turning ANC on/off is useful. 4. The software allows you to create the gesture, which works well. 5. There is no doubt about the built quality. 6. Mics are perfect no problem in calling Cons: 1. It is not possible to connect to two devices at the same time. 2. Reconnecting to your other device takes time; there is no quick switch. 3. The app in the phone only works when linked to the phone; however, you cannot use the app while connected to the laptop. 3. It's difficult to use with your helmet on. Things to keep in mind: 1. If you are moving from a neck band or another device, it will take some time to adapt to this(Any earbuds in this case) 2. Without a protective case, the chance of dropping from your hand is always significant. (https://www.amazon.in/gp/product/B0B6PXLY2V/ref=ewc_pr_img_1?smid=A1S458YIMPYL70&psc=1) 3. This is not a product for runners or gym goers (not designed for it)
Cause_1: Aesthetically appealing
Cause_2: ANC reduces surrounding noise by at least 30% (when nothing is playing) and by up to 80% when something is playing. The simple touch function for switching between tracks and turning ANC on/off is useful.
Cause_3: The software allows you to create the gesture, which works well.There is no doubt about the built quality.
Cause_4: Mics are perfect no problem in calling
Cause_5: It is not possible to connect to two devices at the same time.nReconnecting to your other device takes time; there is no quick switch. The app in the phone only works when linked to the phone; however, you cannot use the app while connected to the laptop. It's difficult to use with your helmet on. Things to keep in mind:If you are moving from a neck band or another device, it will take some time to adapt to this(Any earbuds in this case) Without a protective case, the chance of dropping from your hand is always significant. Product Title: JBL Tune 230NC TWS, Active Noise Cancellation Earbuds with Mic, Massive 40 Hrs Playtime with Speed Charge, Adjustable EQ APP, 4Mics for Perfect Calls, Google Fast Pair, Bluetooth 5.2 (Black)
Review Content: Bought these after using realme q2 ear buds for a year. Did an extensive review before looking to buy a new pair. 1. It's not a great fit. Perhaps all ear buds suffer from this problem. I have to use small size silicon cover to fit. Yet it doesn't feel 100% re assuring. But manageable. 2. Sound quality is clean. Like most reviews said I felt the sound Signature is very neutral. It's good. Almost feel like a low cost audiophile ear buds 3. The app and eq is what does the custom trick. Keep tweaking the eq to hit your sweet spot. And the keep changing as per the gernre. It's. Task but the only way to listen to a variety of music . 4. The mids is general are very crisp. Bass as reviews by many as crisp. It is not. It's just a lean and near bass. Will have to change the eq for a good base profile. 5. These are great for the price point. I guess one can never compare it with a 10k+ ear buds.
Cause_1: It's not a great fit. Perhaps all ear buds suffer from this problem. I have to use small size silicon cover to fit. Yet it doesn't feel 100% re assuring. But manageable.

Task but the only way to listen to a variety of music . 4. The mids is general are very crisp. Bass as reviews by many as crisp. It is not. It's just a lean and near bass. Cause_4: These are great for the price point. I guess one can never compare it with a 10k+ ear buds.

Product Title: JBL Tune 230NC TWS, Active Noise Cancellation Earbuds with Mic, Massive 40 Hrs Playtime with Speed Charge, Adjustable EQ APP, 4Mics for Perfect Calls, Google Fast Pair, Bluetooth 5.2 (Black)
Review Content: I almost lost one bud a few times, even when there was no vigourous movement.. Oil, wax, sweat and hair are part of the ears and cant do much about it.. These buds are made very smoth where it sits in the ears. They shud have been a rough patch on the buds where it fits in the ears, to give some grip. This is the only regret & complaint I have with these buds. Other that that, these are one hellava pair of buds, comparable to bose. I have bose soundsport buds but they are a bit bulky and dont fit under a helmet. I wanted a compact and punchy, powerful buds and this JBL buds fit the bill perfectly. Bass is unbelievably punchy for a 6mm driver. It has a perfectly balanced delivery of the Mids & Highs without any distortion or irritation.

Product Title: JBL Tune 230NC TWS, Active Noise Cancellation Earbuds with Mic, Massive 40 Hrs Playtime with Speed Charge, Adjustable EQ APP, 4Mics for Perfect Calls, Google Fast Pair, Bluetooth 5.2 (Black)
Review Content: I've had wireless bluetooth headphones before but this is a premium product for it's price range. A total segment killer. It has got awesome sound clarity with good bass and low mid responses along with a good and clear treble section. You can equalise the sound as per your needs from the JBL Headphones App that you can download from Playstore or ITunes Store. You can even edit the touch responses from volume control to media control or ANC control using the app. The noise cancellation feature is spot on and this provides 3 different modes of noise cancellation. Charging and battery longevity is really good. Doesn't feel uneasy to wear and doesn't fall off the ears or something. I'd recommend this product to everyone who's looking for a great Bluetooth earphone set in this price range.

Product Title: JBL Tune 230NC TWS, Active Noise Cancellation Earbuds with Mic, Massive 40 Hrs Playtime with Speed Charge, Adjustable EQ APP, 4Mics for Perfect Calls, Google Fast Pair, Bluetooth 5.2 (Black)
Review Content: Sound quality is good across different music generes, which is nice. On call audio quality is average. The person on the other end can hear you but it's low and a bit muffled. When switching from video mode to audio or turning on and off ANC you'll have to wait 5-10 seconds. It takes a bit time so that's not as seamless as you'd expect. It pairs automatically when you open the case but you'll still need to manually switch your bluetooth on. So it's not a no-click process as such. Fits nicely in the ears doesn't seem to be falling off either. Charging is also fast. Overall nice. Sound quality definitely good. Ideally it's worth not more than 4000 in terms of value for money.

Product Title: JBL Tune 230NC TWS, Active Noise Cancellation Earbuds with Mic, Massive 40 Hrs Playtime with Speed Charge, Adjustable EQ APP, 4Mics for Perfect Calls, Google Fast Pair, Bluetooth 5.2 (Black)
Review Content: I regret purchasing the JBL Tune 230NC TWS earbuds as they have proven to be a disappointment from the very beginning. Right from the first days of usage, I encountered persistent connectivity issues. The earbuds would frequently disconnect while I was listening to music or engaging in any other audio activity. Each time this happened, I had to place them back into the charging case and re-establish the connection. Furthermore, I find this product to be severely overpriced solely due to the JBL brand name. After just one month of usage, the left earbud completely stopped functioning, and it no longer shows any signs of charging when placed in the case. This issue has rendered the earbuds practically useless. Based on my experience, I strongly advise against purchasing the JBL Tune 230NC TWS earbuds. The connectivity problems and the subsequent failure of one earbud make it an unreliable and unsatisfactory product. Please consider alternative options before making your purchase.

Product Title: JBL Tune 230NC TWS, Active Noise Cancellation Earbuds with Mic, Massive 40 Hrs Playtime with Speed Charge, Adjustable EQ APP, 4Mics for Perfect Calls, Google Fast Pair, Bluetooth 5.2 (Black)
Review Content: ● The packaging is really good and keeps the box contents safe. ● The earbuds case, buds, eartips and the charging cable are of really good quality. ● Buds have a snug fitting in the ears. I personally like the medium sized eartips on but it totally depends on other factors such as canal opening size, etc. ● Stick design is really good on the 230NC. It comes with buds design too in the 130NC, Do check it out. ● The buds connect quickly to the device, thanks to BT 5.2 and google quick connect. ● Sound quality and the bass is truly dope. ● The sound can be customized through JBL Headphones app according to your preference. ● ANC, Ambient aware and talkthru are the features that fascinated me the most. They work really well and are of great utility. ● Battery life is good. On paper claim is 10 hours for buds and 30 hours for case with ANC off. However, I got around 6-7 hours for buds and around 20-25 hours approx for the case. Obviously depends on your usage too. These buds justify their RS. 5,999 Price tag. A really good deal for people looking for mid range earbuds that offer plethora of amazing features.

Summary:
Comprehensive Summary Review for Mivi Earbuds:
 

 Mivi earbuds have garnered a diverse range of reviews, showcasing both positive and negative experiences. Here's a consolidated overview based on various user feedback:
 

 Positive Aspects:
 

 Sound Quality: Across numerous reviews, users consistently praise the excellent sound quality, impressive bass, and clear audio. The 13mm drivers stand out for their powerful performance.
 Build Quality: Commendations for the build quality, design, and matte finish of the charging case. Many users find the lightweight and compact design comfortable for prolonged use.
 Connectivity: Fast and reliable connectivity, with dual connectivity being highlighted as a convenient feature.
 Battery Life: Generally positive responses regarding the battery life, fast charging capabilities, and the ability to last for extended periods, making them suitable for various activities, including gaming.
 Features: Appreciation for features like touch controls, noise cancellation during calls, and dual-mode, enhancing the overall user experience.
 Negative Aspects:
 

 ANC (Active Noise Cancellation): Some users express dissatisfaction with noise cancellation, particularly during calls.
 Connectivity Issues: Few reports of connectivity problems, including automatic earbud disconnection and challenges in maintaining a stable connection.
 Durability: Mixed opinions on durability, with occasional concerns about the longevity of the product.
 Call Quality: Inconsistent call quality reported by a few users, including issues such as low volume, muffled audio, and occasional disconnections.
 Battery Backup: While many users praise the battery life, there are sporadic mentions of dissatisfaction with the battery backup in certain cases.
 Overall Verdict:
 Mivi earbuds present a compelling option in the earbuds market, with notable strengths in sound quality, design, and various features. The positive feedback on build quality, connectivity, and battery life is countered by occasional concerns about durability, ANC performance, and connectivity issues. The affordability of these earbuds adds to their appeal, making them a value-for-money choice.
 

 Recommendation:
 Considering the mixed reviews, potential buyers should carefully assess their preferences and requirements. Mivi earbuds seem to excel in delivering a quality audio experience, particularly for music enthusiasts. However, individuals prioritizing top-notch ANC or consistent call performance may want to explore alternative options within a similar price range. Overall, Mivi earbuds offer a commendable package, and user satisfaction is likely to depend on individual preferences.

Summary:
Comprehensive Summary Review for Apple AirPods Pro 2nd Generation:
 

 Apple AirPods Pro 2nd Gen have received a mix of reviews, showcasing both positive and negative experiences. Here's a consolidated overview based on various user feedback:
 

 Positive Aspects:
 

 Sound Quality: Numerous users praise the top-notch audio quality, well-balanced mids, lows, and highs, and the punchy bass. Spatial audio with dynamic head tracking is commended for creating an immersive experience.
 ANC (Active Noise Cancellation): The ANC feature is widely appreciated, described as world-class and effective in various environments, making it suitable for travel and noisy surroundings.
 Transparency Mode: The adaptive transparency mode is recognized for working like magic, providing users with a clear awareness of their surroundings when needed.
 Connectivity: Seamless integration into the Apple ecosystem is a significant positive point, with users finding them to be the best choice for iPhone users.
 Build Quality: The earbuds' compactness, lightweight design, and stem controls are appreciated, contributing to a comfortable and premium feel.
 Additional Features: Features like the adaptive mode, spatial audio, and stem controls are highlighted as valuable additions, enhancing the overall user experience.
 Negative Aspects:
 

 Battery Life: Some users express disappointment with the battery life, suggesting that it could have been better.
 Charging Cable: Complaints about the charging cable not being USB-C, as mentioned in the product description, causing confusion and raising concerns about outdated models.
 Amazon Purchase Experience: A few users report issues with Amazon, including receiving defective or used products, open seals, and challenges in getting replacements or refunds.
 Overall Verdict:
 The Apple AirPods Pro 2nd Gen offer an excellent audio experience, especially for users within the Apple ecosystem. The ANC, transparency mode, and spatial audio are standout features, making these earbuds a top choice for immersive sound. However, concerns about battery life and occasional issues with Amazon's purchase experience are noted.
 

 Recommendation:
 For Apple enthusiasts and those seeking a premium audio experience within the Apple ecosystem, the AirPods Pro 2nd Gen are highly recommended. However, potential buyers should pay attention to the battery life aspect and consider purchasing directly from Apple or authorized retailers to ensure a smooth and reliable experience. Overall, these AirPods are a worthwhile investment for users seeking high-quality audio and advanced features.

And it’s double worth it if you have an iPhone 14 or below because of they don’t have usb c anyway. The new usb c model is absolutely identical to this one except for the port. If you have and iPhone 15 or above go for the new one I would say.

Product Title: Apple AirPods Pro (2nd Generation)
Review Content: I have used AirPods Pro but never purchased them as I found them too bright to my liking, but when 2nd generation came, I bought them and I will have to admit that sound quality is really really excellent. I don’t have any complaints with sound quality. Noise cancellation is also pretty good and spatial audio works like a charm with supported content and apps (works best with videos / movies). I have even used AirPods Max and found them too bright but these are perfect. Bass is not boomy but sufficient enough to enjoy and definitely better than 1st Generation. I’d recommend to purchase a silicon case for it because it’s glossy surface is prone to scratches even if you’re using it carefully. Product was delivered on same day with good packing and product was brand new with no issues whatsoever as on date.

Product Title: Apple AirPods Pro (2nd Generation)
Review Content: Even if you already own the 1st generation airpods pro, I would personally highly recommend this upgrade to the 2nd generation of airpods. Everything that the airpods pro did good earlier, these do even better by leaping margins. Especially the ANC & transparency modes are just fab! One more that I noticed and adore that these are even lighter in weight and far more comfortable to wear. Music quality is just phenomenal! Especially the lows and the bass. No words… just go for it. And I loved the same day delivery by Amazon. Order at 2 pm, received by 6 pm! Worth the purchase and upgrade. P.S. Much better upgrade than the iPhone 14s, if you already own a 13. Godspeed & cheers’

Product Title: Apple AirPods Pro (2nd Generation)
Review Content: So if you have been ordering apple products on Amazon thinking that you're covered, think again! I ordered a Air Pod Pro gen 2 - from Appario Retail.. .....and recieved a 1) opened and resealed box (apple seal off, scotch tape on) 2) dirty internal package 3) scrathed/buffed charging case 4) clearly used air pods with ear wax on them! 5) Not only that, its got a missing ear bud (the fresh silicon ones). I tried to put in a repalcement request, and I've been on hold over the phone for an hour since Amazon doesnt allow for a straight through return/ replacement in apple's case, AND the teams been working hard to let me know that I have a "good product" and I shouldnt bother about the reused bit (their words not mine), and if I do insist, the only option is to go to Apple Store for a "resolution" . With no defect, only the fact that its a returned / resued/partial parts product resold to me at full price, it doesnt take much to understand what Apple's response will be. Thats the last time I'm buying a apple product from Amazon !!! Buyers beware! Btw, the hold music is not bad, and one just has to ignore the fact (or not) that they are violating Department of Telecom guidelines with their VOIP calls using a UK number from an India location. P.S the support call was terminated after having been on hold for a reaaallly long time! Wow ! Incompetence!

Summary:
Summary Review:
 

 The Samsung Galaxy Buds Live have received mixed reviews from customers, showcasing both positive and negative experiences. Many users appreciate the earbuds' sound quality, especially in the open-ear design, offering a unique and immersive experience. The bass is praised for its thump, and the clarity in calls and music is highlighted. The earbuds are noted for their comfortable fit for some users, while others find them uncomfortable, especially for long durations.
 

 On the downside, the noise cancellation feature receives varied opinions, with some users stating it's subtle and effective for minimal frequencies, while others find it lacking, especially in comparison to other products. Connectivity appears to be an issue for some users, reporting short-range connections, occasional disconnections, and difficulties with different devices.
 

 The design and build quality of the earbuds and case receive positive comments for their premium feel. However, some users report issues with the case, such as losing caps and difficulties in opening.
 

 Battery life is generally appreciated, with longer durations reported when noise cancellation is turned off. The Samsung Galaxy Buds Live seem to work well with Samsung devices, offering a seamless experience, but connectivity issues with other brands are noted.
 

 In conclusion, the Samsung Galaxy Buds Live offer a unique open-ear design, excellent sound quality, and comfort for some users. However, concerns about noise cancellation effectiveness, connectivity issues, and occasional discomfort for certain individuals should be considered before making a purchase. The product is seen as a good value, particularly when obtained at a discounted price during sales.

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Buds Live Bluetooth Truly Wireless in Ear Earbuds with Mic, Upto 21 Hours Playtime, Mystic Black
Review Content: The media could not be loaded. My ears are pretty long(7cm) and they fit in my canal perfectly as my canal is wider the thickness of one bean is 1.1 cm wide on narrow end which goes in the canal and 1.3 on wider end the charger pin with eartip is in contact with the skin which provides it grip if the small cartilage which pokes out of the skin of ear is big enough your buds will never fall out Pros 1) excellent fitting for my ears I workout everday but these beans won't budge 2) premium and balanced sound quality with amazing bass for half in ear buds bass boost makes even punchier 3) extremely good build quality let's see how long they last 2 days complete 4) battery is sufficient for 4-6 hr use for full charge 5) premium experience with the touch controls they work amazinngly good for 5000rs Cons 1)ANC is weird and creates a weird pressure illusion which you get in the plane making it extremely uncomfortable it works to limited extent and make you feel how you feel when you use silicon tipped earbuds 2)caused earpain after 1-2 hr which is temporary and heals in a minute 3) Sometimes sound crackles and sometimes won't stop until phone is restarted it has some bugs as these have 2 year old optimization CONCLUSION- Bang for the buck in 4990 to 8000rs in 2023 but them now they are better than any airpods out there for the price 4990 Btw I am still confused why has the price dropped so much

Cause_5: premium experience with the touch controls they work amazinngly good for 5000rs

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Buds Live Bluetooth Truly Wireless in Ear Earbuds with Mic, Upto 21 Hours Playtime, Mystic Black
Review Content: These are some of the best wireless buds you can get 4.4k Pros: 1.Music and call quality are good for such an open ear buds 2.Easy pairing, no connectivity issues (by the way I'm using galaxy mobile so i don't know how's the connectivity for other phones) 3.Comfortable fit only for medium to big ears but if your ear size is small better avoid these If you're getting uncomfortable when using the buds aftet some time you're not using them properly try to adjust them in your ear if that doesn't solve the problem you can return the product because it simply doesn't fit your ear 4.Battery backup is also good but i haven't tested them exactly, they'll fulfill your needs, company claims 21 hours with the case and 5-6 hours for the buds Cons: 1.Only con for me was ANC, if you're looking for ANC better avoid these because even these have ANC they're not cancelling the noise properly because of their open ear design When ANC is turned on these buds just cancel out low humming noise but you can hear all the outside sounds and vocals This is my review after using them for a week So if you want good pair of buds with music, call quality and comfortable design by sacrificing ANC then you can consider these buds if you need ANC go for other models.

This is my experience after using it for 3 months :- Sound Quality - Excellent at this price range Battery level- Approx 7-8hrs without ANC with the buds and The case could charge the buds 3rise Noise cancellation: It can cancel out Fan noise , Generators noise but can't cancel out louder ones than that + the thing to note here is these are *Open ear Headphones* are are meant for the audience who look to wear this for longer hours without much discomfort so ANC is just a gimmick out here so don't buy it if your intension is to try out ANC Other than that theres the Samsung Wearable app which i use in my OP8t device which has various presets to customise your audio experience, the bass and the mids and the Highs sound exceptionally well that too with Dynamic preset . THIS is helpful for a student like me who prefers comfort and audio quality and battery life over ANC I use it to listen to my regular pre recorded lectures everyday from morning till night without the need to charge up the case everyday Case quality is top notch and worth it unlike some plastic low quality cases You don't need To own a samsung phone for the good experience unlike apple products . THING TO NOTE : I Brought this product from Amazon during the Diwali sale for ₹3999/-. For this price the product is a steal I would suggest you guys to buy the product if it is priced below 5k anyday but a pro tip: always look out for Festival offers

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Buds Live Bluetooth Truly Wireless in Ear Earbuds with Mic, Upto 21 Hours Playtime, Mystic Black
Review Content: The media could not be loaded. Everything is just topnotch.. Build quality, Sound quality, wireless charging, battery backup are the pros of this buds.. I listened songs on amazon music about 1½ hours at around 65-70% volume and the buds looses only 10-12% of battery which in my opinion is a very good number.. ANC is decent enough, means it will only cut noise of fans and other low noises as it is an open ear design, don't expect total too much.. The only con i am facing that it doesn't support dual pairing.. Every time if you want to connect with a different device you have to unpair this from the 1st one and then it will be visible to the 2nd device.. At the time of buying this I knew that it doesn't switch between 2 devices.. But didn't knew that it doesn't even support dual pairing.. Ofc its not a deal breaker coz rest everything you get is topnotch.

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Buds Live Bluetooth Truly Wireless in Ear Earbuds with Mic, Upto 21 Hours Playtime, Mystic Black
Review Content: The media could not be loaded. I purchased this with doubt as it's the first generation of wireless ear buds from samsung. Actually it's very good! I used to for 2+ weeks and I'll list down the pros and cons. Pros: ● Very clear even with bass boost ● Comfortable in ear headphone ● Wireless charging support. Works very well with Samsung wireless charging pad and reverse wireless charging on my Galaxy S21 FE. ● Decent ANC, could cut out AC noise, rain noise and any other constant noise. ● Intelligent led indicators to indicate battery levels. ● Long battery life. For me it lasted around 4 hours with ANC and 6+ hours without ANC. ● Seamless connection with Galaxy devices. You don't even need to turn on Bluetooth, just press the connect button and it does everything for you after installing setup. ● Microphone quality is great. It picks up voice beautifully even if I talk in a really quiet voice. Cons: ● The touch gestures are not that great. You need to tap it carefully or else it'll misunderstand it for triple or double raps. ● ANC, if you expect a lot from this, you're gonna get disappointed as you can still hear conversations and loud noises clearly. I haven't noticed any other cons till now, will update if I find any in future. Overall, this is a great wireless earbuds for this price range. You can go for it if your budget is around 5k.

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Buds Live Bluetooth Truly Wireless in Ear Earbuds with Mic, Upto 21 Hours Playtime, Mystic Black
Review Content: They sound great. ANC works but only to a marginal extent, however that is exactly what the company advertises (*locks out all minimal frequencies*). Definitely won't block out the sound of an airplane jet but removes the screeching background noises from my neighborhood's construction. Sizing is a bit odd so I don't think it'll fit well with tiny ears. Has extra clips or whatever you call em if you've got huge ears. They did hurt the first 5 minutes i had them on but I've become used to it in just a day. Delivery was superquick (2days to Gwalior, MP). To ensure they fit well you should watch the official *how to put them on* uploaded by samsung. My phone's a Samsung and it works remarkably well with these: great bluetooth range, crisp sound quality and the equaliser settings are pretty useful (the normal mode works just fine but the galaxy wearable app has some more just in case). But with my laptop it isn't the same. Has a creaking sound in the back and poor bluetooth range which might be because of how outdated that laptop is, lol. Battery is great without anc and with anc on it works for 4-5 hours, however i would not recommend having it on because i find it to be a waste of battery. Without anc it lasts a good 8-9 hours. The OG box came in with a charging cable but i have the 25w charger already so it charges like zooom! The case is perfectly fine in itself and feels premium but i might purchase a silicone case to make sure these gems stay in pristine condition ⚡

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Buds Live Bluetooth Truly Wireless in Ear Earbuds with Mic, Upto 21 Hours Playtime, Mystic Black
Review Content: these earbuds are a class above the other 3-4k segment earphones. originally costing around 15k, become absolutely bang for buck under 4k. People who are claiming their ears ae paining are not putting these earbuds right, learn once on youtube how to put these earbuds in and you will be able to wear them without even noticing. I have a pair of Beats studio 3s and powerbeats 3 as well and these actually sound a little better than them just because of that open soundstage that you get with an open ear design. The ANC is just namesake, no noticeable difference, it just clears out very minimal hisses and all. The sound is just unheard of in this price range. I mean under 4k, these are gold. One issue that I am facing is with the ipx2 rating of these, as i am a sweaty person and may just have to switch to my powerbeats for workouts. But still took them to the gym twice and they stay in your ear all the time without even feeling that you are cut off from the world. P.s.- enable bass boost in the app, if you like a little punch.

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Buds Live Bluetooth Truly Wireless in Ear Earbuds with Mic, Upto 21 Hours Playtime, Mystic Black
Review Content: It only looks beautiful but performs really ugly. If you keep your phone in any of your pocket and talk over this Samsung galaxy ear buds live. 50% voice breaks. If you are playing a song over your phone using any music app and keep the phone into any of your pant pocket and try to listen using these buds while walking, about 50% music streaming distortion is guaranteed. Even if you keep your phone at your left hand side or right hand side, hardly 2 feet away, another challenges of latency is always noticed in the other side of the ear bud. It expects you to keep your phone in your palm and in your front while using these buds. YES. I got it for 3999 but trust me it is the most useless Samsung product i have ever used. It is costly even if someone gives it for free. Because usability is very low and painful. The mobile phone to this earbuds connection range in straight clear area is only about 6 feet, after that the voice distorts. If you still want to try first hand then you can pay and try. Remember there is no return policy on this product, only replacement in case of any so called manufacturing defects. So think before investing in it. And in fact think before donating Samsung in the name of Samsung galaxy buds live. And yes not to forget telling than so called ANC is a waste feature in this earbuds. In fact the other party hears more noice than actual while talking over this Samsung galaxy buds live earbuds. Hope this actual review after using 3 weeks helps other folks who are looking for this piece.

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Buds Live Bluetooth Truly Wireless in Ear Earbuds with Mic, Upto 21 Hours Playtime, Mystic Black
Review Content: Fantastic pair of true wireless earbuds with excellent bluetooth connectivity. The sound quality is pretty good too though I'm already spoiled by the excellent sound quality and signature sound of the Galaxy Buds Pro, still the Galaxy Buds Live is a very good companion when you don't want an earbud that goes inside the ears giving an isolating effect. The overall sound is great and its pretty fantastic listening to music with the Buds Live. The Black colour suits my style and is among my favourites. I just wish the noise cancellation was a bit better on these though scientifically its not possible without the isolation effect. The use of mics isn't just enough for cancelling out all or even most of the noise. Call quality is also great on this pair of earbuds. The microphones are great and it can be easily recommended to anyone who's on a bit of budget and is ready to compromise on the level of noise cancellation.

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Buds Live Bluetooth Truly Wireless in Ear Earbuds with Mic, Upto 21 Hours Playtime, Mystic Black
Review Content: TL;DR: Bought it for 5k, not worth it for the price. The ANC is there just for the namesake. You won't even notice the anc if no one told you it's active. The Bluetooth range sucks. Signal gets severely attenuated as soon as I go to an adjacent room. My ₹1000 earbuds have a better range. It's has this peculiar "bean" shaped design which hurt my ears. It's not just annoying that you'll only notice it, it outright hurts your ears (This one would be subjective). Sound quality is good while in proximity to the phone/ device playing audio. Battery is good. Easily lasts over a day. Bought it for ₹5000. Not worth it at all for the price point.
