Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Buds Live Bluetooth Truly Wireless in Ear Earbuds with Mic, Upto 21 Hours Playtime, Mystic Black
Review Content: The time has come... Drum Rolls.... Before I express my utter candid views about the product, I'd like to thank the "seller" and "Amazon" for making this product available online and delivering it on time. Honestly I think I'd be happier if Samsung sold me a piece of rock with their logo on it, that way I'd be sure and content knowing that the rock is useless and it doesn't come with any exaggerated claims. Unfortunately Samsung sold me a failed product, and I can see Samsung laughing at me like "Skeletor" from "He-Man". Now, about the product It just disconnects, and disconnects, and disconnects... I tried using it with my Galaxy S10 mini, LG G8X, S20, Tab S6, Samsung Smart TV, ROG Desktop, Laptop and more, it disconnected with every device. I guess Samsung really wanted to test its potential to make something so unstable that the most unstable element in the periodic table looks far stable than Galaxy buds live, and guess what, they succeeded with flying colors. The product's audio quality isn't great too, it is mid heavy. Everytime I listen to it, it feels as if "AKG Audio" wanted to be better than "Bose", but eventually settled for "Shriram Audio, every rickshaw driver's dream audio". Its noise canceling feature is an added gimmick, with its noise canceling "On" one can probably hear an astronaut landing on moon. Due to all the issues described above, I recently got the product replaced too, but unfortunately all the issues still remain. Sumsung does give you good service, but it should be the last thing one should consider before buying a product. And when it comes to Galaxy Buds Live, definitely stay away... I owned the first generation galaxy buds and they too went bad quite soon, their battery degraded in about 6 months of usage. Moral of the Story Samsung can make good phones, but they can't make good audio products probably ever, and when you see a Samsung audio product next time, buy a piece of "Rock"...

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Buds Live Bluetooth Truly Wireless in Ear Earbuds with Mic, Upto 21 Hours Playtime, Mystic Black
Review Content: First expression when received my Buds live: Its too Smaller than we imagine similar to the size of a Mexican Bean (Rajma) First expression testing sound quality: Highly disappointed, thought my 15K gone, I felt even my Old JBL BT inear worth 2.5K gives me better quality than this, even thought the positive reviews around YouTube are paid. Honestly speaking these pairs of Buds Live slowly practised to fitting my ears, this is something between inear and on ear. After couple of updates these Buddies started giving me mindblowing quality of Sound! With super Bass, Felt premium is premium!!! So this like A.R.Rahman new song which becomes hit slowly. Gaming mode gives u awesome low latency, but no use of it, as Indian Gov Banned PUBG. True Drawbacks: It gives the best loud sound only at Max volume, equalizer normal is Good, others making the loudness down. Sound breaks frequently when you connect ur device in 5Ghz Wifi, fixed when connected to 2Ghz. So if you kinda guys keep thinking to spend 15K for this Buds confused sleepless nights pls stay away. If you kinda freaking Gadget buyer trying all new products go for it!! Final Verdict: Buds Live will changes ur life with a super new experience! Giving it 5 star after testing it for a week.

Overall design is good, quality is good, fancy product, go for it b'coz the price is genuine on Amazon.

Product Title: Acer Nitro V Gaming Laptop 13th Gen Intel Core i5-13420H with RTX 4050 Graphics 6GB VRAM, 144Hz Display (16GB DDR5/512GB SSD/Windows 11 Home/Wi-Fi 6),15.6"(39.6cms) FHD ANV15-51
Review Content: Given the price at which I got the product, Acer Nitro V has taken no prisoners; it has absolutely killed its competitors. I ordered the product on 8th October & received it on 17th. Let me go through the pros of the laptop: 1. Looks - Not one person has had any negative remark on the appearance of my laptop. 2. Latest Hardware - 13th Gen i5 13420H processor coupled with a 4050 75W graphics card. Comes with 16 GB DDR5 ram & 512 GB Gen 4 SSD (usable - around 450 GB). Upgradable RAM & SSD - Upto 32 GB & 2 TB respectively. 3. Speaker Quality - The sound quality of the speakers was surprisingly good. 4. Thermals - Faced no issues as of yet. Watch this space - will update after proper gaming. 5. Weight - Not very lightweight but yes relatively lightweight if one directly compares with a conventional gaming laptop. 5. Keyboard - Single colour (white) illuminated keyboard. The feedback is very good. I don't know whether these are Cons but let me still mention them : 1. Battery Life - Average, to be honest. My personal opinion if you want to save more power would be to decrease the refresh rate & brightness. But it is better to plug in & use the laptop, if you're at your home. It helps the laptop in the long run. And do not run any game without plugging in the charger. It will kill your battery sooner than you can imagine. 2. Display Brightness: Could have been a tad bit on the brighter side. But not a deal breaker, for sure. 3. Camera Quality: Just a basic camera, seriously! Don't have high hopes in this regard. 4. No MS OFFICE - This was a bummer (for me). Sitting on the fence : Build Quality: It is neither a rugged, rough and tough laptop nor absolutely brittle. The lid & keyboard flex were as minimal as it can be. Personally, for me, the build quality is pretty decent. Conclusion: As long as the price of this laptop is under 80k, one should have no doubts whether to buy it or not. Go for it.
Cause_1: Not one person has had any negative remark on the appearance of my laptop.
Cause_2: Latest Hardware - 13th Gen i5 13420H processor coupled with a 4050 75W graphics card. Comes with 16 GB DDR5 ram & 512 GB Gen 4 SSD (usable - around 450 GB). Upgradable RAM & SSD - Upto 32 GB & 2 TB respectively.
Cause_3: Speaker Quality - The sound quality of the speakers was surprisingly good.
Cause_4: Display Brightness: Could have been a tad bit on the brighter side. But not a deal breaker, for sure
Cause_5: Just a basic camera, seriously! Don't have high hopes in this regard.
Summary:
Final Summary Review: Acer Nitro V
 

 The Acer Nitro V emerges as a strong contender in the gaming laptop market, delivering exceptional performance and value for its price. Users have praised its sleek appearance, powerful hardware, and impressive gaming capabilities. The laptop, equipped with a 13th Gen i5 13420H processor and a 4050 75W graphics card, handles a variety of AAA games effortlessly.
 

 Pros highlighted by users include the laptop's appealing design, robust hardware specifications, including 16 GB DDR5 RAM and a 512 GB Gen 4 SSD, and the surprisingly good quality of its speakers. The thermal performance has been commendable, even during extended gaming sessions, with minimal heating reported. Additionally, the laptop is relatively lightweight, making it suitable for on-the-go gaming.
 

 Some users noted potential drawbacks, such as average battery life, a display brightness that could be slightly improved, and a basic camera quality. The absence of pre-installed MS Office and the subjective build quality left a few users on the fence. However, many found these to be minor concerns compared to the overall package.
 

 User experiences with customer service and technical support varied. While some praised the quick and easy resolution process, others faced challenges with defective products and delays in technician visits.
 

 In terms of pricing, users expressed satisfaction, asserting that as long as the laptop remains under 80k, it is a worthwhile investment, offering great value for the features it provides. Some noted that the laptop was purchased during a sale, further enhancing its cost-effectiveness.
 

 In conclusion, the Acer Nitro V stands out as a budget-friendly gaming laptop that delivers excellent performance, impressive thermals, and a sleek design. While some users faced challenges with customer support and specific features, the majority found it to be a compelling choice within its price range, especially when acquired during promotional events. For gamers on a tight budget, the Acer Nitro V is deemed a steal, offering a powerful gaming experience with a few minor compromises.

 Some users noted potential drawbacks, such as average battery life, a display brightness that could be slightly improved, and a basic camera quality. The absence of pre-installed MS Office and the subjective build quality left a few users on the fence. However, many found these to be minor concerns compared to the overall package.
 

 User experiences with customer service and technical support varied. While some praised the quick and easy resolution process, others faced challenges with defective products and delays in technician visits.
 

 In terms of pricing, users expressed satisfaction, asserting that as long as the laptop remains under 80k, it is a worthwhile investment, offering great value for the features it provides. Some noted that the laptop was purchased during a sale, further enhancing its cost-effectiveness.
 

 In conclusion, the Acer Nitro V stands out as a budget-friendly gaming laptop that delivers excellent performance, impressive thermals, and a sleek design. While some users faced challenges with customer support and specific features, the majority found it to be a compelling choice within its price range, especially when acquired during promotional events. For gamers on a tight budget, the Acer Nitro V is deemed a steal, offering a powerful gaming experience with a few minor compromises.

Product Title: Acer Nitro V Gaming Laptop 13th Gen Intel Core i5-13420H with RTX 4050 Graphics 6GB VRAM, 144Hz Display (16GB DDR5/512GB SSD/Windows 11 Home/Wi-Fi 6),15.6"(39.6cms) FHD ANV15-51
Review Content: So, the Acer Nitro V - it's an intriguing choice for budget-conscious gamers, You could get this beast for well under 70k after applying the promotional discounts in the Great Indian Festival. So the review is written while keeping in mind the price point and only focused on gaming. Now, Let's get down to the nitty-gritty. Games Tested: Counter-Strike 2 , Valorant, RDR2, Hogwarts Legacy, TLoU, FH5. The Good Stuff: 1. **Gaming Whiz**: Your can play almost all recent AAA games @ 1080p Ultra at medium to high fps. With DLSS 3 Frame generation you can easily double your fps with minimal loss to the visual fidelity (Only available on RTX 40 Series gpus). So that you can finally take advantage of the "RTX ON" settings . The laptop doesn't come with a MUX switch which is a must for any decent gaming laptops. But you can compensate for that by connenting your external monitor through the HDMI port which connects directly to the GPU. You will notice the difference in FPS in games like Valorant. The 6gb VRAM is a great add on as most laptops in this segment only provide you with a measly 4gb of VRAM (let me tell you, this is a pretty big deal and can be a deal breaker as games are becoming more and more vram hungry day by day. Hogwarts Legacy and TloU, I am looking at you.) 2. **Cool Customer**: Now the laptop performs great in gaming, but how about the thermals? *Spoiler Alert* : Even after long gaming marathons, this thing stays cooler than the other side of the pillow. Hats off to the thermals – Don't know how but Acer managed to cool this puppy down with the 2 fans and the 2 exhausts, both on a single side of the laptop. * Dell G15, take notes. * *Pro Tip* : Always keep the laptop plugged in while gaming and turn on the gaming mode (you can keep fan control to auto). The fans remain super quiet under normal usage but as soon as you hit 60s the fans go hard ( and i mean SUPER hard and you can feel the sound and rumble). If you're a mad man you get an option to put max speed. This unlocks the full potential of the laptop, although I don't recommend it. Rather, put a FPS cap on in the Nvidia settings and game at a consistent smooth FPS. 3. **Slim & Svelte**: A gaming laptop that doesn't double as a dumbbell. It's pretty lightweight at just 2.1 kg, making it great for gaming on the go or lugging to LAN parties or as your travel buddy in your short or long trips. 4. **Keyboard Bliss**: Typing on this thing feels like a dream. The keys are responsive, which makes it not just great for gaming but also everyday typing tasks. 5. **Roomy Trackpad**: Surprisingly, the trackpad is quite large, and the gestures work like a charm. It's got that smooth operator feel. The Not-So-Good: 1. **Meh Build Quality**: To keep the price down, Acer had to make some compromises on build quality. It's not super premium, but it does the job. 2. **Battery Blues**: With a 57WH battery, you can't expect it to last through a gaming session (even half) without plugging in. Keep the charger handy and get yourself a USB- C PD charger to use on the go. 3. ** Same old Display **: Yes, that same old Acer Nitro trademarked 144Hz 250 nits brightness IPS lcd panel, nothing to write home about. Terrible viewing angles but atleast the colors and saturations are okay. Just get a good external monitor. Rather, put a FPS cap on in the Nvidia settings and game at a consistent smooth FPS. 3. **Slim & Svelte**: A gaming laptop that doesn't double as a dumbbell. It's pretty lightweight at just 2.1 kg, making it great for gaming on the go or lugging to LAN parties or as your travel buddy in your short or long trips. 4. **Keyboard Bliss**: Typing on this thing feels like a dream. The keys are responsive, which makes it not just great for gaming but also everyday typing tasks. 5. **Roomy Trackpad**: Surprisingly, the trackpad is quite large, and the gestures work like a charm. It's got that smooth operator feel. The Not-So-Good: 1. **Meh Build Quality**: To keep the price down, Acer had to make some compromises on build quality. It's not super premium, but it does the job. 2. **Battery Blues**: With a 57WH battery, you can't expect it to last through a gaming session (even half) without plugging in. Keep the charger handy and get yourself a USB- C PD charger to use on the go. 3. ** Same old Display **: Yes, that same old Acer Nitro trademarked 144Hz 250 nits brightness IPS lcd panel, nothing to write home about. Terrible viewing angles but atleast the colors and saturations are okay. Just get a good external monitor. And in the "Well, That's Interesting" Department: - The 16 GB DDR5 RAM comes in a single-channel setup, which might not be everyone's cup of tea. Also, it's clocked at 4800 MHz, not the advertised 5200 MHz (Although it does support it). Here is the scoop - Get another 16gb on the second slot and you have 32gigs of RAM. So if you're planning to upgrade RAM in the future then you might save a few bucks. All in all, the Acer Nitro V is a steal for gamers on a tight budget. It's a powerhouse when it comes to gaming and boasts impressive thermals and a sleek design. Just be aware of its minor quirks, like build quality and battery life.

Summary:
Dell G15 5520: A Comprehensive Overview Based on Customer Reviews
 

 Positive Highlights:
 

 Unexpected 16GB RAM Upgrade: Several customers were pleasantly surprised to receive the 16GB RAM variant instead of the ordered 8GB, providing an unexpected performance boost.
 Impressive Speaker and Screen Quality: Users praised the loud speakers and good screen quality, enhancing the overall multimedia experience.
 No Fan Sounds: The laptop was commended for its silent operation, with no noticeable fan noise during regular use.
 Generous Software Bundles: Lifetime Microsoft Office subscription, one-month Xbox, and a 15-month McAfee antivirus subscription were appreciated bonuses.
 Smooth Warranty Claim: Users reported hassle-free warranty claims, debunking concerns raised by some pre-purchase reviews.
 Manageable Thermals: While some mentioned heating issues, others highlighted reasonable thermal performance during gaming, with temperatures remaining between 50-85°C.
 Mixed Feedback:
 

 Battery Life: Opinions on battery life varied, with some users expressing satisfaction for a gaming laptop while others found it below average, lasting around 2.5 to 3 hours with normal usage.
 Charging for Optimal Performance: Suggestions to keep the laptop always on charging for better gaming performance, indicating a reliance on consistent power.
 Constructive Criticisms:
 

 Issues with Dell Customer Support: Some users reported difficulties with customer support, particularly related to returns and memory expansion.
 Concerns about Build Quality: Despite overall positive comments on build quality, a few users expressed concerns about heating and construction.
 Gaming Performance:
 

 Performance Praise: Users praised the laptop's gaming performance, citing smooth experiences with AAA titles and high frame rates in various games.
 Battery Impact on Gaming: Users noted that gaming on battery might lead to reduced performance and increased lag, emphasizing the need to play while connected to the charger.
 Additional Features:
 

 Design and Build: The laptop's sleek and modern design, along with robust build quality, garnered positive remarks.
 Display Quality: High-resolution and vibrant display, suitable for both gaming and multimedia consumption.
 Audio Quality: Commendation for powerful speakers providing an immersive audio experience.
 Fast Charging and Connectivity: Positive mentions of fast charging, latest connectivity ports, and a user-friendly keyboard enhancing the overall user experience.
 Overall Verdict:
 The Dell G15 5520 presents a compelling package for users seeking a powerful gaming laptop within a reasonable budget. While feedback on battery life is mixed, its unexpected RAM upgrades, impressive performance, and additional features contribute to a well-rounded device. Customers are advised to consider individual preferences and requirements before making a purchase, keeping in mind the varying experiences shared by users.

Product Title: Dell G15 5520 Gaming Laptop, Intel i5-12500H,16GB DDR5,512GB SSD,NVIDIA RTX 3050 (4GB GDDR6),15.6"(39.62cm) FHD WVA AG 120Hz 250 nits, Backlit KB Orange, Win 11 + MSO'21,Dark Shadow Grey,2.81kg
Review Content: The media could not be loaded. So, Guys my genuine review for this laptop is I was searching for laptop with specifications of I5 12500h with 3050 and I got G15 in ~₹60k and with this price point I thought this is best deal I'm getting compared to Nitro5 and Tuf and till 5-6 Aug Lenovo Tuf was not available so I purchased This. After getting delivery on 6 August I encountered with it's first error at time of System Setup laptop was unable to detect It's battery it was working only on plug in mode. And i was totally frustrated 🥴 with this product after calling service centre and they replaced the battery in next 3-5 working days. And after service it was working fine untill I found one more issue of (blue screen)unexpected error occurred while keeping my pc on sleep. Still figuring out how to fix this. After 10-15 days of use dell showed it's power a black line occured on screen and again service guy came and replaced the whole screen panel and he said it was occured due to wire cut of display cabel I dont know how the hell a wire which is tucked perfectly can be cut. And still I'm facing heat issues software glitches and many more....... One more important message this laptop does not comes with extra ssd slot dell is misguiding us saying they have one extra ssd 2 slot but when I opened the back panel there was no slot at all. Scam by dell saying upgradable ssd slot. If I just see pros of this laptop its way better than any other under this price whether it is it's performance or playing games doing heavy task it manages everything well. . Sound quality ease of use everything is good. My suggestion is if you are buying this laptop go for Loq or Nitro 5 they are best in segment. Thankyou for reading 🙂

So, Guys my genuine review for this laptop is I was searching for laptop with specifications of I5 12500h with 3050 and I got G15 in ~₹60k and with this price point I thought this is best deal I'm getting compared to Nitro5 and Tuf and till 5-6 Aug Lenovo Tuf was not available so I purchased This. After getting delivery on 6 August I encountered with it's first error at time of System Setup laptop was unable to detect It's battery it was working only on plug in mode. And i was totally frustrated 🥴 with this product after calling service centre and they replaced the battery in next 3-5 working days. And after service it was working fine untill I found one more issue of (blue screen)unexpected error occurred while keeping my pc on sleep. Still figuring out how to fix this. After 10-15 days of use dell showed it's power a black line occured on screen and again service guy came and replaced the whole screen panel and he said it was occured due to wire cut of display cabel I dont know how the hell a wire which is tucked perfectly can be cut. And still I'm facing heat issues software glitches and many more....... One more important message this laptop does not comes with extra ssd slot dell is misguiding us saying they have one extra ssd 2 slot but when I opened the back panel there was no slot at all. Scam by dell saying upgradable ssd slot. If I just see pros of this laptop its way better than any other under this price whether it is it's performance or playing games doing heavy task it manages everything well. . Sound quality ease of use everything is good. My suggestion is if you are buying this laptop go for Loq or Nitro 5 they are best in segment. Thankyou for reading 🙂

Summary:
HP i5-12450H GeForce Graphics 15-fa0666TX: A Varied Customer Experience
 

 Positive Aspects:
 

 High Performance for Video Editing: Users engaged in video editing and graphics work praised the laptop's smooth performance, especially with 16GB RAM and RTX 3050.
 Fast Rendering: A specific mention of the laptop rendering a 4k video in a short time, showcasing its processing power.
 HP Omen Performance Management: Users appreciated the HP Omen feature for effectively managing performance.
 Display Quality: Good brightness on the display, with an acknowledgment that graphic designers might need an sRGB external display.
 Speaker Quality: Positive comments on good speaker quality, with a suggestion to install B&O drivers if issues arise.
 Quick Charging: The inclusion of a 200W charger was noted as an advantage for fast charging.
 Trackpad and Keyboard Comfort: Good trackpad area, comfortable key distribution, and typing experience were highlighted.
 Constructive Feedback:
 

 Weight and Battery Life: The laptop was noted to be slightly heavier, and some users expressed dissatisfaction with low battery life in high-performance mode.
 Backlit Keyboard Levels Missing: Lack of adjustable backlit keyboard levels was mentioned as a drawback.
 Camera Quality: Below-average camera quality led to a recommendation to buy a new one for meetings.
 Cooling Fan Sound Issues: A user reported severe sound issues from the cooling fan within a month, leading to a service center visit.
 Power Button Placement: A significant concern about the power button being placed near the delete button, causing accidental shutdowns.
 Varied Recommendations:
 

 Gaming Performance: While some users didn't focus on gaming, others recommended the laptop for its gaming capabilities, especially with the RTX 3050.
 Graphic Designers' Note: Graphic designers were advised to consider an external sRGB display.
 In Summary:
 The HP i5-12450H GeForce Graphics 15-fa0666TX offers robust performance for video editing and graphics tasks, coupled with features like the HP Omen performance management system. However, considerations around weight, battery life, and issues like power button placement and cooling fan sounds highlight a varied customer experience. Prospective buyers are encouraged to weigh their priorities against the specific use cases mentioned in reviews to make an informed decision.

Camera is below average so for meetings and all you have to buy a New One.

Summary:
Lenovo Laptop Review Roundup: A Mixed Bag of Experiences
 

 Positive Highlights:
 

 Performance and Design: Many users praise the product for its good performance, fast boot-up, and sleek design.
 Display Quality: Positive feedback on the high-resolution display, making it suitable for general use and moderate gaming.
 Gaming Experience: Some users reported smooth gaming experiences, especially for games like GTA 5, Sleeping Dogs, Forza Horizon 5, and God of War.
 Build Quality: Appreciation for the durable build quality and a backlit keyboard.
 Multitasking: Positive remarks about the laptop's ability for multitasking, quick app openings, and a smooth overall experience.
 Lightweight and Portable: Mention of the laptop being handy to carry around, weighing just 2 kg.
 Areas for Improvement:
 

 Quality Control Issues: Several users expressed dissatisfaction with the product's quality, including touchpad problems, low sound volume, and battery drainage issues.
 Service and Support: Complaints about poor technical support, delays in replacement, and unresponsive customer service.
 Defective Units: Instances of receiving defective pieces, with problems related to display, sound, brightness, and touchpad.
 Software and Performance Issues: Reports of software crashes, slow performance, and dissatisfaction with the laptop's gaming capabilities.
 Battery Life: Consistent feedback about poor battery life, especially during gaming and video playback.
 Missing Keys: A complaint about a missing key on the keyboard.
 Challenges in Replacement: Users shared difficulties in getting replacements due to technical support hassles and unfulfilled promises.
 Overall Verdict:
 Lenovo laptops present a mixed picture with some users enjoying a smooth experience, highlighting positive aspects like performance, design, and display quality. However, numerous complaints about defective units, poor battery life, and unsatisfactory technical support raise concerns. Potential buyers are advised to consider these varied experiences and weigh their priorities before making a purchase decision.

Summary:
Fire-Boltt Smartwatch Review Roundup: Style Meets Functionality
 

 Positive Highlights:
 

 Display Quality: Users consistently praise the vibrant AMOLED display, with many finding it visually appealing.
 Design and Build Quality: The sleek and stylish design of Fire-Boltt smartwatches receives positive feedback, enhancing the overall fashion statement.
 Connectivity: Easy and smooth Bluetooth connectivity with both Android and iOS devices.
 Features: Users appreciate the variety of features, including health tracking, fitness modes, and Bluetooth calling.
 Battery Life: Generally positive remarks on battery life, with users mentioning decent performance and quick charging.
 User-Friendly Interface: The intuitive and easy-to-navigate user interface is highlighted as a positive aspect.
 Value for Money: Many users find the smartwatches to offer good value for money, considering the features and style.
 Areas for Improvement:
 

 Accuracy of Sensors: Some users express concerns about the accuracy of health-related sensors, particularly in blood pressure measurements.
 Battery Life Concerns: A common complaint is that the battery life falls short of expectations, especially when using features like Bluetooth calling.
 Connectivity Issues: Several users report occasional connectivity problems, including disconnection from paired devices.
 Display Lag: Some users mention occasional lag or slow response in the touch screen and display, affecting the overall experience.
 Software Features Missing: Users highlight the absence of certain software features like touch-to-wake, rise-off to wake-off, turn-off screen on covering, and auto-brightness adjustment.
 Build Quality Issues: Few users note concerns about the build quality, including issues with attaching the band to the dial.
 Limited Watch Faces: Complaints about the limited options for watch faces and the time-consuming process of changing them.
 Overall Verdict:
 The Fire-Boltt smartwatches offer a stylish design and a range of features at an affordable price point, making them attractive to many users. Positive feedback on display quality, ease of use, and overall aesthetics suggests a favorable impression. However, concerns about sensor accuracy, occasional connectivity issues, and battery life limitations should be considered by potential buyers. The Fire-Boltt smartwatches seem to strike a balance between style and functionality, providing a viable option in the budget-friendly smartwatch market.

Review Content: A review I wrote after 10 days usage. The Fire-boltt Phoenix Amoled Edition smartwatch is a dazzling piece of technology that effortlessly blends style and functionality. Its stunning AMOLED screen, framed by almost imperceptible bezels, is a visual treat, offering vibrant colors and sharp details. The fast charging feature ensures you spend more time enjoying its beauty than tethered to a charger. Wearing the Fire-boltt Phoenix is a tactile delight as it fits comfortably on the wrist, making it a true fashion statement. The user-friendly interface makes it a breeze to navigate, catering to both tech-savvy and novice users alike. However, the Achilles' heel of this smartwatch lies in its battery life, which falls short when compared to others in the same price range. On a full charge, it manages approximately 36 hours, even less when connected to your phone for Bluetooth calling. The sleep timer's inaccuracy might be a minor annoyance for those tracking their slumber. While the Fire-boltt Phoenix offers a heart sensor and SpO2 readings, its reliability falters when it comes to blood pressure measurements. It's essential to use this watch for its other features, appreciating its style, beautiful display, and ease of use, but perhaps relying on a dedicated medical device for health data.

Summary:
Final Summary Review:
 

 The Samsung Galaxy Watch 4 has garnered generally positive feedback, praised for its impressive design, vibrant AMOLED display, and seamless integration with Samsung Galaxy devices. Users appreciate the advanced health and fitness tracking capabilities, including ECG and blood pressure monitoring, along with real-time coaching for maintaining an active lifestyle.
 

 While the LTE activation process is swift, and compatibility with apps like Google Maps is lauded, the rotating bezel, though stylish, may trap dust over time. Strap quality receives mixed opinions, with concerns about durability and difficulty in detachment and attachment.
 

 A notable concern revolves around battery life, with varying user experiences. Some achieve up to 1.5 days on a charge, while others express dissatisfaction with faster drainage, particularly under heavy usage. The slow charging time, taking around 2 hours, is also criticized.
 

 Opinions on the transition to Wear OS from Tizen are mixed, and fitness enthusiasts find inaccuracies in GPS tracking, heart rate monitoring, and body composition readings. Sleep tracking is reported to be subpar, and returning faulty products poses challenges in customer support.
 

 Despite these issues, users highlight the watch's accuracy, AMOLED display, and smooth touch response. Compatibility for Samsung Galaxy users is emphasized, while non-Samsung users may encounter limitations.
 

 In conclusion, the Samsung Galaxy Watch 4 offers a top-notch smartwatch experience with style, functionality, and health-tracking features. While the mixed reviews highlight concerns about battery life and fitness accuracy, the positive aspects make it a compelling choice for those seeking a comprehensive smartwatch experience. Potential buyers are advised to carefully consider their priorities before making a purchase.

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Watch4 Bluetooth(4.0 cm, Pink Gold, Compatible with Android only)
Review Content: I had been on the lookout for a smartwatch to keep track of my walking, sleeping, heart rate and for music, etc. I looked for options online but nothing quite seemed to fit my requirements at the budget i had. The watch 4 lte version had everything i expected from a smartwatch but exceeded my budget. I decided to settle and go for the bluetooth version. Luckily, just a few days later, i was pleasantly surprised by the discount of the lte version! Ordered it immediately along with a spigen armor strap. The watch arrived and it was everything i wanted and more. Answering calls on the phone is clear and easy. Setting alarms, timers, etc is so much more convenient. There are still features i have not yet used. There is just so much packed into such a tiny thing. I knew about the short battery life and its not much of an issue for me as i charge it whenever im sitting on my pc. I ordered the 40mm size and it fits my 16.5 cm wrist perfectly. Its been 2 months now and i cant come up with anything negative to say.

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Watch4 Bluetooth(4.0 cm, Pink Gold, Compatible with Android only)
Review Content: Look, there are three type of smartwatch/bands categories: 1) Smart bands or fitness bands which is available at lower price bracket, the functionality of watch is very specific with very limited options. 2) Smartwatch with custom os (actually not true smartwatch) these watches are in mid range category and they're very usable with upto 70% functionalities but still you can't call it a 'true smartwatch' because you can't do anything else in them, their features are only limited to what they've been designed. 3) True smartwatch: just like a smartphone, they're capable of doing anything what you can do in a smartphone. Apple ios and Android are only two OS which are capable to run in these smartwatch. Even higher price range watch have LTE with which you can even make calls without your smartphone and even access internet. Watch 4 lte support esim, if you're with jio you can get a duplicate esim and same number will work on smartphone as well as watch. Now this Samsung galaxy watch 4 is android smartwatch with Samsung's custom UI, this watch has Android's later wearOS 3 which is not even available in any other watch. Fossil gen 6 is the only watch which will receive this update in 'future' means it's still running wearOS 2. Some queries i want to solve looking at reviews, people don't know something so they just try to return it on amazon and if they can't they just put a bad review in frustration. 1) Imported watch? If you're buying 'discounted watch' here means the cost is less than the Samsung's original price then definitely that watch is imported from uae or anywhere but that doesn't affect anything. Buy from Appario instead if you want indian version, change the seller please. 2) Battery life? Do you have a smartphone which can work for 7 days in a single charge, no? There's no true smartwatch ever made in the entire world which have a battery life of more than 48 hours. I'm talking about ios and Android os only (even the latest apple series 7 works for 12hours max only in a single charge with normal usage) so that's a thing, you have to charge it daily for approx 1.5 hours like you charge your smartphone. I'll add more things here in future.

Review Content: I got the 40mm one which didn't fit well, so returned. Pros: • Fitness tracking is almost accurate. • UI is good. • Health features are crisp, can we lived with. Cons: • Battery life lasts 24-36 hrs in real time. • Screen wake up with hand raise doesn’t work well when riding a bike wearing this. • Battery discharges fast when all features are enabled, assume 24 hrs on a full battery. My takeaways: • Go with the right size, if you’re a guy with typical wrist size go with 44mm (like I’m 25 with average physique) • Go for LTE variant.

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Watch4 Bluetooth(4.0 cm, Pink Gold, Compatible with Android only)
Review Content: The media could not be loaded. The watch is full of features which you haven't thought yet about. It measures what it says with accuracy and never disappoints to notify stuff going on your phone while its away. Lets cut to the catch, the battery sucks. While it fits comfortably on your wrist all feature packed, the battery hardly stays for 27hrs and much less with full brightness on. Continuous heart rate and stress monitoring can be turned off to conserve and extend a little longer. If you turn off the device it takes roughly 2hrs to reach full charge from 0 to 100, this slow rate is due to the wireless recharge over the traditional wired ones. I would suggest this is a good deal because wearing the any watch for long periods could cause skin irritation and swelling over the wrist. Its been a week since I got the device, today the return period closes and I'm happy I got this over all the current competitors

Review Content: It is for sure an amazing watch. I'd say battery life is decent but not great. Im fine with it though. But the bezel is quite a hassle, it traps dust and ever since i got it like a month ago, it has never felt the same as it did when i unboxed it. It got a little stiff after just one week. But it is such a great help for navigating through the watch UI. Although most google apps aren't optimized for it like the google alarm, i can't stop or snooze an alarm with the bezel. That needs a little attending to. Rest the watch is really great unlike any other. Quite accurate and packs a bunch load of features in it. Amazing watch faces and the fact that i don't have to rely only on the Samsung wearable app for watch faces, makes it a better choice for people who are into styling the watch with premium watch faces. I'm loving it so far. If you want it, go for it. Don't think too much. (I have an additional accesory on - Ae Mobile bezel ring, got it from amazon)

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Watch4 Bluetooth(4.0 cm, Pink Gold, Compatible with Android only)
Review Content: I bought this for 13980, initially I was a bit hesitant to buy it thinking about the authenticity issues but the product arrived intact and i registered it on the Samsung website too. So the seller is genuine and if you getting a deal in the same price or less than don't hesitate to buy just go for it. Now coming to the watch, I wanted to buy watch with small circular dial as the bigger ones doesn't suit my wrist. So I had reviewed almost all the watches feature wise and size wise this was best at the price that i got. Touch is completely smooth no issues there, O2 sensor, heart rate, BMI works completely fine. However for the ECG thrid party app is required if you are not using samsung phone. There are some other options in the watch which are only compatible with samsung phone but i have seen YouTube videos that by using third party apps such features can be explored. Only one issue is there which is about battery, you will get only one day backup. I think it won't be much of an issue as you can turn off the continuous monitoring and extend it as per your convenience. Dialling and receiving the call is also smooth no issues faced. Go for it if you are thinking to buy it from long time.

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Watch4 Bluetooth(4.0 cm, Pink Gold, Compatible with Android only)
Review Content: I recently bought and used a Galaxy 6 classic LTE watch for two days, but I need more experience. However, the latest version of this watch remains the same as Galaxy 4 & 5 with only a few minimal changes. My biggest issue was the battery backup, which depleted from 100% to 0% in just 4 hours and 2 minutes, even without high-end applications installed and regular Bluetooth pairing. Overall, I had to charge the watch three times a day before going to bed. Another significant problem was with the LTE ESIM Pairing. I faced an error during the setup and visited Airtel & Samsung direct stores for help... The Samsung store technicians tried to enable the ESIM process using a Samsung phone by placing my SIM card, and it started pairing correctly. However, the only issue is allowing me to dial superior Emergency numbers. Based on the inputs I received from Samsung store techies, I revisited the Airtel store to verify this signalling issue... Unfortunately, Airtel's technical team identified that Galaxy 6 watch details/data were unavailable in their database, and the ESIM process couldn't connect to the Airtel DNS server... Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Watch4 Bluetooth(4.0 cm, Pink Gold, Compatible with Android only)
Review Content: It's the best Android smartwatch as long as you don't need to use the ESim/LTE on the watch, as it only works with Samsung smartphones. So if you have a Samsung smartphone, it's fine, but if you don't - ONLY BUY the BLUETOOTH version of the Watch5 pro Personally, in India, I think that Samsung has the most reliable Android Wear OS smartwatch collection, however, if you want standalone calling, messages and other app notifications enabled through LTE/esim & you don't have a Samsung smartphone, another potentially good option could be Xiaomi S2 Pro smartwatch which has launched in China in the last few weeks and can be expected in India in a few months. This smartwatch has great specs and a promising battery life.Again compatibility with other Android smartphones has to be confirmed, but knowing Xiaomi's strategies, I assume that they will allow LTE/esim access with other Android smartphones as well. So another tough choice for Android Wear OS smartwatch lovers. PS. The Google Pixel watch 2 being sold in India doesn't have esim/LTE capability, so have to wait for that version in India, which if/when it launches could be a great option. The battery life is only a day or 24 hours and durability is not the best with the exposed glass face. I haven't considered smartwatches from other brands like the Fossil or even Mobvoi is due to their spotty track record in supporting their smartwatches with timely Wear OS firmware/OS updates.

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Watch4 Bluetooth(4.0 cm, Pink Gold, Compatible with Android only)
Review Content: Watch looks great, the display quality is good. The rotating dial is perfect and adds to the style. With Android Wear OS, multiple app support is great. Workout reps/sets counted correctly, when the grip on the wrist is tight. I changed the strap for a better grip. The watch also automatically detects workout. But the progress monitoring is not available. Hope to app development.. Heart rate/Stess monitoring throughout the day works correctly. It would make sense if the watch or app can interact with user to reduce the stress when it reaches the peak. Hope some app development may add this feature sooner. Body fat/skeletal muscle measurements are great to monitor progress. You need a saparate scale to measure body weight each time. Steps counting works. Blood oxygen measurements work correctly. Fall detection is on, but have not tested yet. The watch prompts when you are sitting idle for more than an hour. Sleep tracking report are not very impressive. Many times it shows awake even when you are not. Trying to change my sleeping habits to see the changes. Taking calls over watch works well if the surrounding is not very noisy. The speaker is not extremely loud like phone. Battery life is sufficient for a day. Blood pressure/ECG are not supported in India. However, it is not really a deal breaker for me considering the fitness and Smart OS features.

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Watch4 Bluetooth(4.0 cm, Pink Gold, Compatible with Android only)
Review Content: I was using gear s3 frontier since 2.5 Years and wanted an upgrade. I considered watch active 2, but just because watch 4 switched to wear os, 16GB memory and a better processor decided to get this one. The experience has been largely similar to my gear s3 despite this being a wear os watch. UI is more or less the same, battery back up is also similar. Playstore hasn't made a huge difference in the sense that it doesn't offer drastically more usable / quality / sensible apps than galaxy store. Hope this will improve in future. The app options are nowhere near apple watch. Apple watch has more usable companion apps like amazon music, swiggy, myagte etc whereas galaxy watch doesn't have many options. Hope choosing wearos over tizen paying more money will pay dividends over time.
Cause_1: 16GB memory and a better processor decided to get this one.
Cause_2: UI is more or less the same,
Cause_3: battery back up is also similar.
Cause_4: Playstore hasn't made a huge difference in the sense that it doesn't offer drastically more usable / quality / sensible apps than galaxy store. Hope this will improve in future. The app options are nowhere near apple watch. Apple watch has more usable companion apps like amazon music, swiggy, myagte etc whereas galaxy watch doesn't have many options.
Cause_5: Hope choosing wearos over tizen paying more money will pay dividends over time.

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Watch4 Bluetooth(4.0 cm, Pink Gold, Compatible with Android only)
Review Content: DONT BUY IF YOU WANT ACCURATE FITNESS READINGS OR A FITNESS PROFESSIONAL. SAMSUNG JUST MAKING US FOOLS WITH ITS BRAND VALUE. ------------------------------------------------ cons Fitness 1) GPS tracking is very bad and it always miss tracking some portions while cycling. 2)Heart rate tracking is worst. It will suddenly miss or stop tracking while cycling all the time. 3)Body composition fails to read 8 out of 10 times and it always says moisturize your finger, don't move even I am not moving. 4)sleep tracking is very very bad and inaccurate. Didn't find the watch recording the afternoon short sleeps. I some time woke up midnight 2 for washroom and it didn't record sleep from them. 5)bp and ecg not available in India but you can enable it. event those are 100% inaccurate. got same configured default bp reading when used to my grandfather also. Battery. 6)charging time is very high. nearly 2hours to full charge. 7) battery discharges quickly. Design and speaker 8) need few more holes to the strap. I have 44mm. bit bulky to my thin hands. band is not bending fully below the watch hence while looking straight on to the watch, you may also see big bands towards the 2 ends of the watch screen. 9)watch speaker sound is very low. you cannot use it for calling when in you are outside. ----------------------------------------------- pros 1)new impedance sensor to know full body composition. 2)44mm super Amoled display is beautiful and 1.4inch is big enough 3)BP and ECG are available but not officially. you can enable it via some methods 4) it's a google wear OS now. you can install apps like your smartphone. 4)easy to reply and type due to multiple keyboards available in wear OS 5)can call and receive via smartwatch. get easy to full dial pad and all contacts, messages 6)you can customize, reorder every option, button, menu easily due to wear OS. 7)watch UI is smooth and crispy. rarely observed few hiccups. 8) huge variety of official and 3rd party watch faces available in the store 9) 100s of workout modes and automation workout detection. it takes 10 minutes to detect workout but that will be tracked. Note: Hoping all these cons can be fixed in future software updates.
Cause_1: GPS tracking is very bad and it always miss tracking some portions while cycling. 2)Heart rate tracking is worst. It will suddenly miss or stop tracking while cycling all the time. 3)Body composition fails to read 8 out of 10 times and it always says moisturize your finger, don't move even I am not moving. 4)sleep tracking is very very bad and inaccurate. Didn't find the watch recording the afternoon short sleeps. I some time woke up midnight 2 for washroom and it didn't record sleep from them. 5)bp and ecg not available in India but you can enable it. event those are 100% inaccurate. got same configured default bp reading when used to my grandfather also.
Cause_2: Battery. 6)charging time is very high. nearly 2hours to full charge. 7) battery discharges quickly.
Cause_3: Design and speaker 8) need few more holes to the strap. I have 44mm. bit bulky to my thin hands. band is not bending fully below the watch hence while looking straight on to the watch, you may also see big bands towards the 2 ends of the watch screen.
Cause_4: 9)watch speaker sound is very low. you cannot use it for calling when in you are outside.
Cause_5: new impedance sensor to know full body composition. 2)44mm super Amoled display is beautiful and 1.4inch is big enough

Product Title: Samsung Galaxy Watch4 Bluetooth(4.0 cm, Pink Gold, Compatible with Android only)
Review Content: Bought the Galaxy Watch 4 Classic 42mm Pros: 1. Super sharp and clear amoled display. 2. The bezel is 100% worth the extra money! That tatcile feel when scrolling is unbeatable. 3. Steel version looks very good👌 4. Not too heavy as the reviews suggested. Cons: 1. HORRIBLE...HORRIBLE battery life! It'll drop 10% if you look at it the wrong way. I realise now why people hated WearOS. It barely lasts a whole work day. What's the point of having all these cool features if they HAVE to be turned off to get a barely decent battery life?? 2. The default strap makes the watch stick out and makes it seem larger than it actually is. Fortunately you can get much better 3rd party straps. 3. Accessories for the watch are extremely rare and very overpriced. 4. I maybe the only one who experienced this but the setup failed 3 times. Not very intuitive. Tip: If you're confused which size to buy, I have a 6 inch wrist and the 42mm is perfect size. Conclusion: Samsung has to do something about the battery life. It's awful. Until then people are better off getting the Tizen versions. They lasted 3 days easily.
Cause_1: Super sharp and clear amoled display. 2. The bezel is 100% worth the extra money! That tatcile feel when scrolling is unbeatable. 3. Steel version looks very good👌
Cause_2: Not too heavy as the reviews suggested.
Cause_3: HORRIBLE...HORRIBLE battery life! It'll drop 10% if you look at it the wrong way. I realise now why people hated WearOS. It barely lasts a whole work day. What's the point of having all these cool features if they HAVE to be turned off to get a barely decent battery life??

Review Content: The media could not be loaded. I learnt a lot about the smartwatches in the last 10 days. Especially with the Samsung galaxy watch 4. 1- The E-SIM is not officially supported for all devices in India. I have OnePlus 8 pro and till date no oneplus phone have E-SIM support. And i regret it after i ordered Galaxy watch 4 LTE 44mm. E-Sim Only in few high end device's of samsung and apple phones. However there is still chance of getting this LTE support for Jio users by Jio everywhere option. 2- When coming to the hardware specs of Watch 4, In Android it's the best in the market right now and the only wear os supported watches are (Samsung, Fossil). And also don't expect good battery life in the LTE version. Finally I'll get to the point 😂... Watch 4 classic Bluetooth 46 mm is the perfect one!! (Big super amoled display, 32-35 hrs battery backup). And the bezel ring believe me it's the best part in the watch. ❤️💯 I hope my detailed review will be helpful.

Final Summary Review:
 

 Customers have shared diverse opinions on the Apple Watch SE 2, offering insights into its strengths and drawbacks. The general consensus appreciates the sleek design, quality display, and extensive features of the watch, making it a great addition, especially at its price point.
 

 Positive remarks focus on the watch's aesthetics, comfortable fit, and compatibility with Apple's ecosystem. Users find the watch suitable for daily use, fitness tracking, and maintaining a healthy lifestyle. The seamless integration with iPhones is highlighted, emphasizing the convenience of managing settings directly from the phone.
 

 However, a common concern is the battery life, with mixed experiences reported. While some find it sufficient for a day or more, others express disappointment, suggesting the need for daily charging. Charging speed is generally noted as acceptable, but the battery's longevity remains a notable consideration.
 

 Fitness tracking features, including workout modes and heart rate monitoring, are praised, but there are occasional criticisms regarding accuracy in sleep measurement. The absence of certain advanced health features like ECG and oxygen monitoring in the SE model is mentioned, but this limitation is generally accepted given the lower price point.
 

 The device's performance, user interface, and call quality are commended, with users finding it responsive and efficient in handling various tasks. Some drawbacks include difficulty in downloading music from third-party apps and the absence of support from third-party retailers for certain users.
 

 Despite some negative feedback, the Apple Watch SE 2 appears to be a popular choice for those entering the Apple ecosystem or seeking a reliable and functional smartwatch without the premium price tag. The mixed reviews highlight considerations such as battery life and feature preferences, encouraging potential buyers to carefully evaluate their needs before making a purchase.

Review Content: I felt that this watch is not so accurate in sleep measurement but is fine for most uses. You can turn on the watch for the first time only if you have an iphone. If you are planning to buy the se2 watch then, it is better to not buy the cellular version as most of the tasks can be done without cellular connectivity. If you are away from household wifi then dont worry the watch will instantly connect with the data from iphone using bluetooth without actually activating the hotspot, so the battery of iphone wont drain substantially. As an apple ecosystem user i did not find any practical use of watch in my daily tasks , the only use i could think of was tracking workout or receiving calls without actually touching the phone hence not distracted. EDIT 1 [AFTER 2 MONTHS] - Watch has a few scratches and the band has a few friction marks, rest is good 👍🏻. Battery lasts about 1.5 days without low power mode and using 90 minutes of workout app. EDIT 2 [after 4 months]- The watch band is a bit dirty and not new looking. I tried washing band but it wont go away easily. Watch display has no new scratches. Battery health is at 96% and a bit slower while switching between apps. Sleep measurement is a still a mess.

Review Content: Apple is always in a league of it's own in terms of quality. Review Content: I have an I phone and was in the market for a smart watch/tracker to track my workouts and sleep seamlessly. I was reluctant to pay 32K for a smartwatch when there are good options from other brands such as Amazfit for half the price. Since I did not have the budget for a Series 8 went with the SE 2022. This is the best decision that I have made in terms of procuring gadgets. The watch connects seamlessly with your iPhone and you can use your iPhone to manage your watch's settings completely. Let me list out the clear pros and cons I felt: Pro's - Seamless Integration with iPhone - The excellent Call quality (you don't have to raise your wrist to speak) - Tracks so many workouts (I play Table Tennis it has tracking for almost all sports) - Excellent Sleep Tracking - My screen time on my phone is down by 30% as I don't pick it up that often - Had some accidental bumps but the glass is scratch free so far - 2-day battery life (but I charge it daily from 50%-100% before sleep | which takes ~45 mins) - Excellent heart rate detection (very accurate) - Has loads of apps and replying to messages is very easy via voice, and hand gestures for short replies (it does not feature a keyboard) Cons: - Always on Display (not a deal breaker for me but is an issue for bike and motorbike riders) Key Points: - You will most probably not miss the ECG and Temperature functionality. - All the above stats are with continuous heart rate monitoring and at least 90 mins of activity. - If this is your first apple watch this is the best choice. Hope This helps :)

Review Content: The Apple Watch SE 2 is a great device that offers a lot of features at an affordable price point. It boasts a bright, crisp display that is easy to read even in bright sunlight. The watch is also incredibly snappy and responsive, with a speedy processor that makes using the device a joy. The taptic engine is another standout feature, providing precise and subtle haptic feedback for notifications and alerts. One of the key selling points of the Apple Watch SE 2 is its calling capabilities, and it does not disappoint. The sound clarity for both incoming and outgoing calls is excellent, and the watch seamlessly integrates with your iPhone to make and receive calls without needing to take your phone out of your pocket. However, one of the main drawbacks of the Apple Watch SE 2 is its battery life, which lasts only about a day on a single charge. This can be frustrating for those who want to use the watch all day without needing to recharge it. Another issue with the Apple Watch SE 2 is the difficulty some users experience in downloading songs from Spotify. Apple recommends using Apple Music instead, but this may not be ideal for users who prefer Spotify. Additionally, some users have reported difficulty finding support for the device from third-party retailers such as Amazon. Overall, the Apple Watch SE 2 is an excellent device for those looking for a high-quality smartwatch with calling capabilities and a responsive, snappy interface. However, users should be aware of the limitations of the battery life and potential issues with downloading music from third-party apps.

Summary:
Final Summary Review: Noise Smart Watch
 

 The Noise Smart Watch has garnered mixed reviews, amalgamating both positive and negative feedback from users. Here's a comprehensive overview:
 

 Positive Aspects:
 

 Quality and Durability: Users appreciate the durable construction, ensuring longevity. The overall design and build quality are praised, making it an attractive accessory for various occasions.
 

 Customization: The watch offers customizable watch faces and a variety of strap options, allowing users to personalize their device according to their preferences.
 

 Value for Money: Many users find the watch to be a good value for money, with positive remarks about its performance and features in relation to its price.
 

 Battery Life: The watch boasts impressive battery life, lasting several days, providing convenience for daily use without frequent charging.
 

 Features: Equipped with various features such as sleep tracking, heart rate monitoring, SpO2 measurement, and multiple sports modes, the watch enhances its functionality.
 

 Concerns Raised:
 

 Bluetooth Calling: Some users express a desire for Bluetooth calling functionality, which is absent in the current model.
 

 Mixed Durability Experiences: While some users praise the watch's durability, others report issues with the strap breaking within a short period, raising concerns about overall longevity.
 

 Application Issues: The NoiseFit app, especially the iOS variant, receives criticism for being challenging to pair with the watch, syncing issues, and difficulties in downloading watch faces. The overall user experience with the app is not satisfactory.
 

 Customer Service: A few customers share negative experiences with Noise's customer service, citing issues with responsiveness and disconnection during calls.
 

 Accuracy Concerns: Users report inaccuracies in features like step counting, sleep tracking, and heart rate monitoring, potentially impacting the reliability of health-related data.
 

 Connectivity Issues: Problems like disconnection when the watch is a short distance away from the phone are highlighted as a concern.
 

 Conclusion:
 The Noise Smart Watch appears to offer good value for money with its impressive battery life, variety of features, and attractive design. However, concerns about durability, application issues, and accuracy in health-related features may affect the overall satisfaction of users. Potential buyers are advised to carefully consider their priorities and requirements before making a purchase, keeping in mind both positive and negative feedback from existing users.

Product Title: Noise ColorFit Pulse Grand Smart Watch with 1.69"(4.29cm) HD Display, 60 Sports Modes, 150 Watch Faces, Fast Charge, Spo2, Stress, Sleep, Heart Rate Monitoring & IP68 Waterproof (Jet Black)
Review Content: Writing a review in detail after using the product for last 1 week, i will be straight as possible. Watch: This is an acceptable product in this price range (bought for 2499/-). Design is smooth, material look durable and good quality. (It seems manufacturer is determined to copy apple watch style). Minimum functions. Sports mode has around 8 options (NO SWIM MODE, even though they boast it is IP68). Screen size is ok with good clarity. Battery seems holding as they claim (I have not activated automatic heart rate monitor, may be thats a reason battery holding). So if you are looking for a show piece or imitating smart watch, this is an ideal choice Application (NoiseFit ios variant): Worse than worst mobile app as of now. I have no postive comment regarding app. It was easy to install at around 120 MB, but pairing with watch is difficult, it takes ages to pair and some time not even pairing even though app detect the watch. Now when it get paired I cant sync any data from watch to mobile. When try to manually sync, its just shows *syncing* but nothing happens. So what use of smart watch if you cant record and sync data?!!!. Another issue with app is downloading watch faces. Only on initial pairing time I was able to download a watch face,(The app shows lot of cool dial faces, but what use if you cant USE them ??)remaining time when i tried in app it just shows *downloading ... 0%*, what nonsense is this, i mean if you are launching a product, make sure atleast it works properly and do what you market it will do. For last one week i tried installing/uninstalling app, restarting mob, pairing/unpairing/forgeting device but data syncing was possible only one time that also for a session. Very bad application/interface/watch firmware or whatever it is. So if you are buying smart watch for logging your activities and monitoring exercise regime, better dont buy this product. You can have a mi band for less price with loaded functions and a smooth application. Customer care: Initially raised a complaint for data syncing inability and what they did was forwarding a technical FAQ link for all their product. Being a tech pro, i had already applied all of their troubleshooting options so i replied that Problem persist, at last a customercare officer called and unfortunately i was entering a lift with boss, so told her to please call after 10 minutes. I tried to call back the number afterwards but it was not connecting. Believe me they called back again but even before ringing, disconnected the call and immediately came an sms stating they were not able to reach my number!!!, literally i was waiting for the call and i saw their number just flashing and disconnecting even before attending the call..!!!, speechless at the customer service of Noise, may be those customer care executives might be getting lots of call as they churn out product after product and people raising complaints after complaints. Winding up: Watch is good looking and smooth, but interface is very very bad coupled with strange customer care response. So buy in your own risk and for those interested in atmnirbar bharath, do check were it is manufactured. Will try to update after 4 weeks or if i get any updates...

Product Title: Noise ColorFit Pulse Grand Smart Watch with 1.69"(4.29cm) HD Display, 60 Sports Modes, 150 Watch Faces, Fast Charge, Spo2, Stress, Sleep, Heart Rate Monitoring & IP68 Waterproof (Jet Black)
Review Content: The media could not be loaded. Pros: 1) Sleep tracking is very very accurate! 2) Very light weight and comfortable strap 3) Quick reply option only available in this watch under this price ( bought it for 1699/-) 4) Messeges comes to my watch first and then it comes to mobile 😂😂 5) Blood oxygen is also accurate if you keep your hand close and don't move. 6) Distance travelled is quite upto the mark 7) You can feel the vibration on alarm and find my device 😂 8) Charging time is more than I expected since I kept all the features on and from 100-14 % on the seventh day 😅 not bad in this price segment. 9) Weather readings are accurate , drink water reminder is nice. 10) Very quick charge 45 mins apprx full charge 11) Activity modes - No problems faced while using all of them. But data isn't 💯 accurate. 12) Customizable watch face ! But only time and date is shown in customised faces no other data like steps and calories displayed like other in built faces. ( No one would tell you this in any review!) Cons 1) Out of 10 only 6 times it gets wake on raise the hand -not accurate sensor (update may fix this) 2) Step counting is all wrong and no use! (Update may fix this) 3) connectivity issues - syncing issues , (update may fix this) 4) Once u unpair all the readings from ur watch are gone , only if you have logged into the account and synchronised the watch u can have that in mobile ( internet is required for sync idk why!?) 5) It doesn't show in connected devices in mobile bluetooth but is connected, idk it's a flaw but I think it is 6) Needed more watch faces ! Only 2-3 watch faces I liked . 7) Heart rate isn't accurate but every watch will provide the same in this segment 😅 I faced many problems in start before application and firmware update but now I'm satisfied. Product Title: Noise ColorFit Pulse Grand Smart Watch with 1.69"(4.29cm) HD Display, 60 Sports Modes, 150 Watch Faces, Fast Charge, Spo2, Stress, Sleep, Heart Rate Monitoring & IP68 Waterproof (Jet Black)
Review Content: For someone looking to buy a SMARTWATCH at a less price and with good features please read my review. It has been one month of daily use and have had no complaints till now. Although I did face some issues syncing the phone and the watch in the initial few days. But a few restarts did the job. All the features work fine. I have also noticed that whenever there is a delayed alert on the watch it is mostly due to network issues or if the phone is away from the watch. The watch is not to be blamed. At times, I get notifications a sec earlier than the phone. The feature of replying back to calls with template msgs is only available in noise watches I think. I also have a Boat xtend and it only has the feature to reject calls. The green colour is actually a dull green colour so unless you are sure about the colour don't buy a green one since you won't have an option to return it only bcos u don't like the colour. However, A FEEDBACK FOR THE MAKERS - THERE IS NO REASON WHY NOISE PULSE should HAVE LESS WATCHFACES THAN YOUR OTHER MODELS. Update your user manual and make it easier for those who are using a SMARTWATCH for the first time. Your user manual does not state anything about how to sync it with the phone to get notifications etc. One has to figure it out on the app with trail and error method. It took me a whole day to sync the phone with the watch and figure out what was going wrong. In the end, No electronic gadget is perfect. If you are looking for something near perfect then buy an Apple watch. Else Noise pulse and similar other models are certainly a good buy.

I have also noticed that whenever there is a delayed alert on the watch it is mostly due to network issues or if the phone is away from the watch. The watch is not to be blamed. At times, I get notifications a sec earlier than the phone.
Cause_2: The feature of replying back to calls with template msgs is only available in noise watches I think. I also have a Boat xtend and it only has the feature to reject calls.
Cause_3: The green colour is actually a dull green colour so unless you are sure about the colour don't buy a green one since you won't have an option to return it only bcos u don't like the colour.

Your user manual does not state anything about how to sync it with the phone to get notifications etc. One has to figure it out on the app with trail and error method. It took me a whole day to sync the phone with the watch and figure out what was going wrong. In the end, No electronic gadget is perfect. If you are looking for something near perfect then buy an Apple watch. Else Noise pulse and similar other models are certainly a good buy.

Product Title: Noise ColorFit Pulse Grand Smart Watch with 1.69"(4.29cm) HD Display, 60 Sports Modes, 150 Watch Faces, Fast Charge, Spo2, Stress, Sleep, Heart Rate Monitoring & IP68 Waterproof (Jet Black)
Review Content: The media could not be loaded. I brought this product for tracking my distance i walk and run on daily basis. Cost me 1999₹ Worked well for couple of days in beginning. Thereafter it had some issues. 1.During running in sport mode the watch used to pause automatically in between without any idea.. so i have to check again and again. Or else it indicates less distance then i actually covered. 2. Watch started rebooting again and again which erases data and thus bring every count to zero (ref video). Which is frustrating. 3. We have to connect to noise mobile app which is easy to connect. But as you go 3-5 mtr away it disconnects so find my phone option becomes useless. Talking about application it is really slow. 4. You get about 60 watch faces in mobile app but every time you upload new face to watch which takes 30+ sec to update.. the old one does not get stored in watch so again if you need the old one we have to go back to application to search and change. 5. The watch does not lit up quickly by motion sensor, it takes few attempts to lit if the screen. Or other option is button Good thing about it is touch which is smooth easy interface. Probably good battery life as i used it of 5 days in one charge still has 45% approx. Light weight. Display quality is also good. Visible in sunlight also. I have asked for replacement, as it has some issues. Will get back soon with updated review. Thank you!

Review Content: The Watch is feature rich.The mentioned battery life is 7 days but if you're a normal user it can last up to 10+ days.The display looks like an amoled display even though it's just TFT lcd.I bought in an offer for ₹1199 but now it's ₹1899.I don't think it's worth for ₹1899.Also the watch strap feels kinda plasticy,it also gets dirty really easily.You can buy it if it's price drops down to about ₹1300-1500.The sleep tracking seems okay.If I wake up for a few minutes and sleep again it doesn't record the sleep after I woke up.The heart rate and SPO2 sensors seem legit and doesn't show results of you are not wearing it. Update: The product I received was defective and stopped working (due to water damage). I complainted to noise and they gave a brand new watch.But the one I got from Amazon was made in October 2022 the one noise sent me was made In July. The sleep tracking in this is really accurate unlike the last one.

Review Content: The media could not be loaded. I am writing this after more than five months of using the watch. It's a great quality watch at this budget. Battery life is simply awesome. Review Content: Product quality is good. I have tested it for waterproofing and it turned out good. It is durable. I am someone very messy to use gadgets but so far, no scratch on screen. Touch is fine. BT music works good. Battery could have been better though, it lasts upto over 7 days only. But i see some issues which could have been better: 1. Step translation is not proper. If you link with Google account, it will exaggerate the steps you have taken leading to a false data for your analysis. This could be issue specifically between noise and Google fit. (Images attached of same time.) 2. Alarms can be set in application but cannot be renamed. So you would get the alert but you might not be able to rename why you have set it. PS only noise app alarms can be synced to watch. Android alarms are not supported 3. There are multiple times when I have observed that phone is in my pocket, device is connected, but still call alerts do not reflect on watch screen. Attached images to show and support my observation

Review Content: So, I am writing the review of this watch after using it for 10 Days. I must say, It’s an excellent product in this price range. The watch is very durable as used with high quality materials. The tracking sensors work fairly well, thou steps sensor counts 8 to 9 steps more, it can be resolved with an update ! Accuracy of this watch is between 80 to 85 percent which is quite fair enough at this price point. I am using it with my iPhone 11 & the app performs really well. The noise app is full of options & watch faces will blow you away thou it takes about a minute to upload a watch face. The app also works seamlessly with Apple Health default app & gives you more information of your tracked data of your entire day activity. Raise to wake feature works perfect & in the end the battery life of watch is really amazing, it gonna last you for at least 4 to 5 days or more when paired with your phone. Till date I have only charged it twice in last 10 days. To sum up, if you want a great quality watch with minimalistic features, Go For It guys …. I hope it helps you in your buying decision ✌️ Noise Pulse Grand (Champagne Grey Color) iPhone 11

Bad points I am still trying to figure out how to track my gym strength workout. I am sure there is a way. The noisefit app is nice gives complete detail of steps, calorie count. The build quality is plastic so it doesn't look classy I guess with this price range this is what you will recieve. I am yet to check the sleep monitor. The drinking mode doesn't alert though I have activated it. Will have to check in detail. For anyone who is planning a smart watch first time you can go for it. This won't disappoint you.

Product Title: Noise ColorFit Pulse Grand Smart Watch with 1.69"(4.29cm) HD Display, 60 Sports Modes, 150 Watch Faces, Fast Charge, Spo2, Stress, Sleep, Heart Rate Monitoring & IP68 Waterproof (Jet Black)
Review Content: This is the first smartwatch I have bought Talking about battery: it's excellent. Display is of average quality. Build quality of watch module is not so soothing it looks like very cheap plastic material. But straps are good. Integration of watch faces in app with watch can be improved. Sadly you can't use it's app offline to change watch faces. Everytime you have to download the watch faces , it doesn't saves offline. It would be better if noise provides stress monitor as well. By the way i am happy with this product. Probably this is the one of the best smartwatch under 2500. After 4 days: Does spo2 and heart rate monitor in smartwatches really work ?? I am asking this as amazingly it also measures spo2 and heart rate of water, other liquid, and some solid reflecting objects also 🙄 Another issue is if i am in vehicle it increases the steps even i am not doing any physical activity. Syncing of noise fit with Google Fit doesn't work even after many try.

Final Summary Review: Comprehensive Overview of Various Customer Reviews
 

 The Noise Smart Watch has received a diverse range of reviews, with users sharing both positive and negative experiences. Here's a detailed overview based on the feedback:
 

 Positive Aspects:
 

 Build Quality and Design: Users appreciate the durable construction and design, making it an attractive accessory for different occasions.
 Customization: The availability of customizable watch faces and strap options is well-received.
 Value for Money: Many users find the watch to be a good value for money, praising its performance and features relative to its price.
 Battery Life: The impressive battery life, lasting several days, is a significant positive for daily use.
 Features: Equipped with various features like sleep tracking, heart rate monitoring, SpO2 measurement, and multiple sports modes, the watch enhances its functionality.
 Concerns Raised:
 

 Bluetooth Calling: Some users express a desire for Bluetooth calling functionality, which is absent in the current model.
 Durability Issues: Mixed experiences with durability, with some users reporting strap breakage, raise concerns about overall longevity.
 Application Issues: Criticism of the NoiseFit app, particularly on iOS, for difficulties in pairing, syncing issues, and challenges in downloading watch faces.
 Customer Service: Negative experiences with Noise's customer service, citing issues with responsiveness and disconnection during calls.
 Accuracy Concerns: Users report inaccuracies in features like step counting, sleep tracking, and heart rate monitoring, impacting health-related data reliability.
 Connectivity Issues: Problems such as disconnection when the watch is a short distance away from the phone are highlighted.
 Additional Feedback:
 

 Fastrack New Limitless FS1 Smart Watch: Positive feedback for its display, Bluetooth calling, impressive battery life, and diverse features. Some mention non-functional sleep tracking, inconsistent Alexa performance, and limited notification display.
 Issues with Other Brands: Various users report issues with other brands, such as slow charging, touch screen responsiveness problems, and difficulties with customer service.
 Conclusion:
 While the Noise Smart Watch offers good value for money with its battery life, features, and design, potential buyers should consider the mixed feedback on durability, application issues, and accuracy in health-related features. The Fastrack New Limitless FS1 Smart Watch receives positive reviews, but individual preferences and priorities should guide the decision. Users also face challenges with smartwatches from other brands, emphasizing the need for thorough research before purchasing.
